<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractabacpolicydecisionpoint> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractabacpolicydecisionpoint";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/abacpolicydecisionpoint.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:abacpolicydecisionpointsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractabacpolicydecisionpoint>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractabacpolicydecisionpoint>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractabacpolicydecisionpoint>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointlifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointlifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The decision point reads the current resource policy, audits, and sets a replacement, while request evaluation is authorization-server-first when a token is present, falls back to a static permission backstop when the resource is unregistered or the server is unavailable, denies fail-closed on policy denial, and requests step-up on insufficient auth level. Policy administration and per-request evaluation are distinct flows over the same guard metadata.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:abacpolicydecisionpointsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State is each guarded route's resource, scope, and required permission, plus optional resource-policy records and a decision result that is one of granted, policy-denied, insufficient-auth-level, server-unavailable, or resource-not-registered, with a static permission fallback. The decision is derived per request rather than stored.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:abacpolicydecisionpointsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Routes declare an explicit required permission, resource, and scope consumed as a policy-enforcement point, and resource-policy writes sit behind tenant auth-settings permission with audit-before-adapter mutation. Authorization itself is the permission gate for every protected operation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:abacpolicydecisionpointsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The operation surface is resource-policy read and replacement plus the per-route resource and scope guard metadata consumed by the request pipeline and the query authorizer. Decisions are returned to callers rather than persisted as contract output.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:abacpolicydecisionpointsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Unknown or unregistered resources degrade only to the static permission backstop, an absent static permission denies, an injected resource policy may allow without a static permission, and wildcard policy names are accepted. Validation never opens an unregistered resource by default.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:abacpolicydecisionpointsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Policy denial maps to 403, insufficient auth level maps to a step-up-required/401, a missing expected token maps to authentication-required/401, and static fallback without a permission maps to 403; every path is fail-closed by default. Server unavailability is an explicit non-decisive degradation, not an implicit allow.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:abacpolicydecisionpointsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Resource-policy mutations emit an audit-before-change event and audit failure prevents the adapter mutation, while read-only authorization checks are logged or returned rather than audited per request. Audit precedes any policy change.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:abacpolicydecisionpointsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is invariant-ready for the local policy seam, and authorization-server unavailability and resource-not-registered are explicit degraded, non-decisive states with a static fallback rather than a fake allow. Degraded mode keeps read-only readiness and audit visible.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:abacpolicydecisionpointsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Unit proofs cover the decision logic and resource-policy administration and a runtime proof covers permission-before-entitlement policy ordering, demonstrated in source lineage via hermetic state/policy-chain validation. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:abacpolicydecisionpointsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:abacpolicydecisionpointuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The abacpolicydecisionpoint capability is explicitly API-only; no human-rendered surface, component, action, journey, consent prompt, or renderer input is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:abacpolicydecisionpoint> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:accessibilitya11ygatesemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "accessibilitya11ygatesemanticsource";
