<urn:usf:semanticcontract:apikeyspersonalaccesstokens> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractapikeyspersonalaccesstokens>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractapikeyspersonalaccesstokens> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractapikeyspersonalaccesstokens";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractapikeyspersonalaccesstokens>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:apikeyspersonalaccesstokens>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractapikeyspersonalaccesstokens> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractapikeyspersonalaccesstokens";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/apikeyspersonalaccesstokens.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractapikeyspersonalaccesstokens>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractapikeyspersonalaccesstokens> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractapikeyspersonalaccesstokens";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/apikeyspersonalaccesstokens.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractapikeyspersonalaccesstokens>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractapikeyspersonalaccesstokens>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractapikeyspersonalaccesstokens>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenslifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenslifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "API key lifecycle is explicit: creation returns a plaintext secret exactly once, listing exposes metadata only, authentication validates a live non-revoked secret, and revocation sets a revoked timestamp after which authentication returns no actor. The plaintext secret is never persisted or re-shown.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokensstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokensstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State is active versus revoked, with creation and last-used timestamps, an optional expiry, a revoked timestamp, a key prefix, scopes, and hash/salt storage fields. The plaintext secret is explicitly not part of persisted state.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenspermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenspermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Tenant operations require tenant API-key read/write permissions and operator read requires the platform API-key read permission, and creation additionally requires an API-access entitlement that is deny-by-default. Tenant isolation prevents one tenant from listing another tenant's keys.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenscontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenscontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The operation surface lists, creates, and deletes tenant keys, reads developer context, and provides an operator read of a given tenant's keys. Creation returns the one-time secret; all other reads return metadata only.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokensvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokensvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Creation is rejected for tenants without the API-access entitlement, invalid key identifiers are rejected at the route, and garbage, wrong, hash-presented, or expired secrets never authenticate. Cross-tenant listing is prevented.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenserrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenserrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Usecase results include a not-entitled and an ok variant, invalid route identifiers return 400, and revoked or malformed secrets authenticate as no actor; provider failure returns a typed degraded result fail-closed. Authentication failures never leak whether a key existed.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokensauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokensauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Creation and revocation emit key-created and key-revoked audit-before-change events, and a failing audit aborts creation before the key is stored. Metadata reads are not audited as mutations.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokensreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokensreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is always-on once the data substrate is migrated, and degraded mode disables store-dependent mutation while keeping read-only readiness and audit visible. Live proofs skip honestly when the substrate is unavailable and never fake-pass.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokensproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokensproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "A unit proof covers key lifecycle and authentication, and runtime proofs validate the live repository, crypto, and row-level isolation plus live route-handler behaviour including entitlement gating, demonstrated in source lineage via hermetic/runtime validation. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:apikeyspersonalaccesstokenssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokensuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:apikeyspersonalaccesstokensuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The apikeyspersonalaccesstokens capability has one framework-neutral UI semantic model with explicit surfaces, view models, components, journeys, permissions, accessibility, localisation, and target-specific renderer contracts. This semantic closure disclaims product parity, human acceptance, accessibility compliance, and launch-language readiness.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:apikeyspersonalaccesstokens> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:auditofprivilegedaccesssemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "auditofprivilegedaccesssemanticsource";
