    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:backupandrestore>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "ebfd763f507433c58b440570aad7560ca9f5e7757ddcce8fa9b69ff7481cd1cb";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/backup-and-restore.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:backupandrestore> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractbackupandrestore>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractbackupandrestore> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractbackupandrestore";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractbackupandrestore>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:backupandrestore>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractbackupandrestore> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractbackupandrestore";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/backupandrestore.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractbackupandrestore>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractbackupandrestore> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractbackupandrestore";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/backupandrestore.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:backupandrestoresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractbackupandrestore>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractbackupandrestore>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractbackupandrestore>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestorelifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestorelifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Backup and restore are operational scripts, not an owned schema: backup dumps the canonical relational database and compresses it to an owner-only, version-control-ignored local artifact, while restore destructively overwrites a target database from such an archive. Scope is the canonical relational store only; rebuildable cache, the analytical mirror, and object storage have no platform backup script because they are not canonical state and recover via provider-native lifecycle. The capability owns no tenant records, so its backup scope is configuration and evidence and a restore cannot itself create tenant data.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:backupandrestoresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestorestatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestorestatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "There is no owned database schema; the durable artifact is the compressed dump file written with a restrictive umask and owner-only file permissions to a git-ignored local artifacts location. Restore consumes one such archive and replaces the target database wholesale. Recovery posture for non-canonical stores is explicit: cache is rebuildable, the analytical store is a mirror, and object data is provider-managed, so none participate in this script's state.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:backupandrestoresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestorepermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestorepermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Both operations are guarded environment-gated operator actions. Backup refuses to run outside development or test environments unless an explicit allow-environment override names the target, so a shared database is never quietly dumped. Restore refuses unless the environment is development or test AND a confirmation token matching the exact environment is supplied, making the destructive overwrite intentionally hard to trigger by accident.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:backupandrestoresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestorecontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestorecontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract is a pair of operations: produce a timestamped compressed dump of the canonical database, and restore a named compressed dump over a target database, each subject to its environment guard. Backup owns no tenant data and restore cannot fabricate tenant data; for higher environments disaster recovery uses a stage-equivalent managed snapshot rather than these local scripts. These scripts already encode the destructive-operation controls the platform requires and are intended to be reused unchanged.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:backupandrestoresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestorevalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestorevalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Backup validates the environment guard (refusing non-dev/test environments absent the explicit allow override) before dumping; restore validates both the dev/test environment constraint and the exact confirmation token before overwriting. The stage-level destructive-allowed and data-preservation settings from the environment registry further gate whether destructive operations may run at all in a given stage.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:backupandrestoresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestoreerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestoreerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The operations fail closed: a missing or non-matching environment override or confirmation token aborts before any destructive action, and a script failure leaves the target database untouched rather than partially applied. There is no owned tenant data, so the dominant risk is semantic drift or configuration loss rather than tenant-row loss; provider (dump/restore tooling) failure surfaces a typed degraded or readiness failure without fabricating success.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:backupandrestoresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestoreauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestoreauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Backup artifacts are written with owner-only permissions to a controlled, git-ignored location so dumps are not inadvertently exposed or committed. Operator actions are environment-gated and explicit, leaving the override or confirmation token as the human-attributable signal that a destructive operation was deliberately authorised. Promotion and readiness proof logs record that the backup proof executed.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:backupandrestoresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestorereadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestorereadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness reflects whether the backup path can produce a valid artifact in the current environment under its guard; when the dump or restore tooling is unavailable the capability degrades, disabling the destructive path while keeping read-only readiness visible. Readiness being blocked, a failed backup proof during promotion, or repeated typed errors over threshold raise alerts. Restore is never part of normal readiness flow because it is destructive and confirmation-gated.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:backupandrestoresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestoreproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestoreproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by the local backup proof, which demonstrates the guarded dump path end to end against the canonical store. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:backupandrestoresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestoreuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:backupandrestoreuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The backupandrestore capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:backupandrestore> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:brandingandthemingsemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "brandingandthemingsemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:sfd19a3923236a2d4337726193cbc6444cd7d9b64dca8b80001f40cf03b3a1a36>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:brandingandtheming>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "4010a27d57aca18660d2df796a7f0f093f8e5560c88a1362443158f8552e5965";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/branding-and-theming.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:brandingandtheming> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractbrandingandtheming>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractbrandingandtheming> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractbrandingandtheming";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractbrandingandtheming>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:brandingandtheming>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractbrandingandtheming> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractbrandingandtheming";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/brandingandtheming.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractbrandingandtheming>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractbrandingandtheming> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractbrandingandtheming";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/brandingandtheming.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:brandingandthemingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractbrandingandtheming>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractbrandingandtheming>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractbrandingandtheming>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandtheminglifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandtheminglifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Branding resolves from a default theme overlaid by tenant theme overrides into an effective theme response used to bootstrap the client shell, while richer branding edits (such as application name and theme selection) flow through the configuration registry as managed override definitions. The lifecycle therefore spans an unauthenticated bootstrap read and audited, permissioned branding mutations through the configuration plane.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:brandingandthemingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State comprises a static default theme plus tenant-scoped theme override keys consumed by the runtime theme response, alongside registry-managed branding definitions (application name typed as a string and a theme selection constrained to system/light/dark). Bootstrap theme state and editable branding-registry state are kept distinct so the pre-auth response stays simple while managed edits carry full definition semantics.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:brandingandthemingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The theme bootstrap read is unauthenticated and host-derived so the client shell can style itself before login, whereas registry-based branding edits require tenant-scoped configuration read/write permissions with per-definition permission enforcement. Branding overrides are tenant-isolated through the same configuration plane, so a tenant only ever reads or writes its own branding values.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:brandingandthemingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract surface is a bootstrap theme read that returns the effective theme for the resolved host, plus the configuration registry's list/patch/delete operations scoped to branding definitions. Both paths sit behind the configuration-store port and adapter, so theme delivery and branding management share one persistence contract expressed abstractly.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:brandingandthemingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Theme reads tolerate missing or failed tenant resolution by returning defaults rather than erroring, while branding edits validate through the configuration registry: the theme selection is constrained to its allowed set and the application name is type-checked as a string. Branding mutations inherit the registry's full validation of overridability, value type, and permission scope.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:brandingandthemingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Theme read failures are non-blocking and fall back to the default theme so the client shell can always render, whereas branding mutations use the configuration error mapping for validation, forbidden, unknown-key, and non-overridable outcomes. The bootstrap path is deliberately fail-open to defaults while the management path is fail-closed.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:brandingandthemingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The theme bootstrap read is read-only and emits no mutation audit, while branding configuration mutations emit value-changed or value-cleared audit actions before the tenant settings are written. As with the configuration registry, the audit precedes the persistence change for every branding edit.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:brandingandthemingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Theme delivery is degraded-to-default when the tenant settings store or tenant resolution is unavailable, ensuring the shell still styles itself; configuration-managed branding is invariant-ready once the persistence substrate is reachable. Degradation is explicit and bounded to falling back on defaults rather than failing the request.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:brandingandthemingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandthemingproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by configuration unit proofs covering branding definitions, override source, validation, and audit-first writes, together with route-level coverage of the theme bootstrap response and its default fallback. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:brandingandthemingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandtheminguisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:brandingandtheminguisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The brandingandtheming capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:brandingandtheming> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingsemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingsemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:sfedd4830511fd818c1e965254a6409be1456a5a7b12baec2800cac71db9f07b3>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "bfce36cbb0dfc80154189211def0f38b25b09d9c10ba252ac636929b9eb29bbb";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/browser-telemetry-grafana-faro-rum-and-browser-to-bff-tracing.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractbrowsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractbrowsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractbrowsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractbrowsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractbrowsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractbrowsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractbrowsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractbrowsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractbrowsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractbrowsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractbrowsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractbrowsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracinglifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracinglifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Captures browser real-user-monitoring (RUM) telemetry and propagates distributed tracing from the browser through the backend-for-frontend, so a single user interaction appears as one correlated trace spanning client and server. The browser SDK emits to a collection endpoint that forwards to the trace/log backends; the capability is provider-backed, owns no tenant records, and must keep its lifecycle/readiness model stable across extraction.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "It owns no database schema: RUM events and browser spans are emitted to a collection receiver and forwarded through a collector to the trace and log backends (e.g. Tempo and Loki), with only contract/config and a readiness record held locally. Trace context is propagated from the browser to the BFF so client and server spans join into one trace, and behaviour changes update semantic artefacts rather than introducing owned state.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The telemetry collection endpoint is treated as a controlled ingress under standard platform security controls; since no tenant rows are owned, isolation is carried as scoped attributes (tenant/request/trace context) on the emitted spans rather than row-level data. Ingestion fails closed on missing or invalid configuration rather than accepting unscoped telemetry as authoritative.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Exposes a browser telemetry collection contract and OTLP browser-trace propagation to the trace backend behind ports/adapters, so the RUM SDK, collection receiver, and collector are swappable without changing the contract. Trace context propagation across the browser-to-BFF boundary is the load-bearing semantic, and emitted metric/span names follow the stable per-capability convention.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Incoming browser telemetry is validated for shape and required trace/correlation context before forwarding, and missing or invalid configuration fails closed instead of inventing defaults. Span and attribute names are kept within the controlled, OpenTelemetry-informed vocabulary so arbitrary client-supplied names are not accepted as canonical.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Provider or pipeline failure returns a typed degraded/readiness failure and never fabricates a successful collection or trace; repeated typed errors crossing a threshold are an explicit alert condition. The capability owns no tenant data, so the dominant failure risk is semantic drift or configuration loss, and mutation boundaries stay closed under failure.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Configuration and contract changes to the telemetry pipeline are tracked as auditable platform actions correlated to request and trace identifiers, even though no tenant records are mutated. Audit and observability signals must agree with collected proof output when a correlation or readiness claim depends on a given browser-to-BFF trace.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness reflects whether the RUM SDK, collection receiver, collector, and downstream trace/log backends are wired and healthy, degrading explicitly when any stage is unavailable while keeping read-only readiness and audit visible. Emitted readiness, error, and audit signals use the controlled, OpenTelemetry-informed observability vocabulary without claiming OpenTelemetry compliance.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by the cited browser-to-BFF tracing end-to-end proof, which force-flushes a single Tempo trace spanning the browser app and the platform API along the observability-correlation ladder, demonstrating client-to-server trace joining as hermetic/runtime lineage rather than a current-readiness claim. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracingsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracinguisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracinguisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing capability is explicitly internal; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:browsertelemetrygrafanafarorumandbrowsertobfftracing> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
