<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractcodequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractcodequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractcodequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractcodequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractcodequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractcodequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractcodequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractcodequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractcodequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractcodequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractcodequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanninglifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanninglifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The security-gate lifecycle defines static rules and configuration, runs a static-analysis error gate, verifies SBOM baseline freshness, enforces SBOM license/security policy, validates code-scanning configuration and database behaviour, exposes a security-control route, and fails closed in authoritative mode. These are global-operator CI/build gates rather than tenant-facing runtime surfaces.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State includes static-analysis rule severities, the SBOM baseline document and lock hash, SBOM policy audit output, code-scanning config/database/result state, security-route registration, and the global security-console clickthrough readiness. The state is configuration and evidence rather than owned tenant records.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The security control surface and the security-console clickthrough are operator/global-only and explicitly not tenant-safe, while the static gates are repository-controlled rather than runtime tenant permissions. There is no tenant-scoped access to the global code-quality consoles.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Contracts are the static-analysis gate, SBOM verify, SBOM policy, and code-scanning validate commands, the rule and code-scanning configuration files, and registration of an operator security route. These are CI/static contracts plus one global-operator route, not a tenant API.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Validation checks static-analysis error findings, SBOM file integrity and lock hash, license/security policy, code-scanning binary/config/database behaviour with an authoritative fail-closed mode, and route registration. Where configured, a locally absent code-scanning tool may honestly skip rather than silently pass.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Static-analysis error findings, a missing or stale SBOM, policy violations, missing code-scanning in authoritative mode, an invalid code-scanning configuration, or an absent route all fail non-zero. Authoritative mode fails closed so a missing gate cannot be treated as a pass.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "These static gates produce build evidence and reports rather than runtime audit rows; route access and provider/security changes are audited by their owning runtime capabilities. The gate output and evidence links are the durable record.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is gate success plus optional security-console/service readiness from platform service probes, with missing local tools classified honestly according to each script's mode. Readiness fails closed on missing or stale evidence rather than assuming success.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by static-analysis, SBOM verify/policy, code-scanning validate, security-test, and security-control-route checks asserting fail-closed gate state and route registration. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanningsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanninguisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanninguisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The codequalityandsecretanddependencyscanning capability is explicitly internal; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
