    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "5a9c367c6396401211d127ed24d95aedfce21168054a839b39952e80d819f79c";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/configuration-registry-and-history.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:configurationregistryandhistory> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractconfigurationregistryandhistory>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractconfigurationregistryandhistory> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractconfigurationregistryandhistory";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractconfigurationregistryandhistory>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:configurationregistryandhistory>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractconfigurationregistryandhistory> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractconfigurationregistryandhistory";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/configurationregistryandhistory.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractconfigurationregistryandhistory>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractconfigurationregistryandhistory> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractconfigurationregistryandhistory";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/configurationregistryandhistory.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:configurationregistryandhistorysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractconfigurationregistryandhistory>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractconfigurationregistryandhistory>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractconfigurationregistryandhistory>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistorylifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistorylifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "A configuration definition moves through active, deprecated, and internal states, and the runtime resolves an effective value per tenant from either the platform default or a tenant override. Setting an override performs an audit-first upsert and clearing it performs an audit-first delete, after which a best-effort change-notification event is emitted; the audit precedes the persistence mutation so the change is always recorded.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:configurationregistryandhistorysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistorystatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistorystatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State is split between a pure, serialisable registry of configuration definitions (each carrying storage key, value type such as string/enum/boolean/json, allowed values, tenant-overridability, lifecycle, and per-definition read/write permissions) and the persisted tenant override values. The effective value carries a source marker distinguishing platform default from tenant override, and feature-flag compatibility transforms are applied during resolution.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:configurationregistryandhistorysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistorypermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistorypermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Reads require a tenant-scoped configuration-read permission and additionally filter the visible definitions by each definition's required read permission; mutations require a tenant-scoped configuration-write permission and the use case re-enforces each definition's required write permission. Feature-flag definitions require dedicated feature permissions, and all resolution is tenant-isolated so one tenant never observes another tenant's overrides.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:configurationregistryandhistorysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistorycontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistorycontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The interface exposes a list operation filterable by category that returns serialised definitions paired with effective value and source, a patch operation that sets a single key's override from a supplied value, and a delete operation that clears an override. Operation semantics are mediated by a configuration-store port with a persistent adapter so the contract is independent of the storage technology.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:configurationregistryandhistorysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistoryvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistoryvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Validation rejects unknown keys, non-overridable definitions, missing values, enum values outside the declared allowed set, and type mismatches against the definition's value type, and it honours category filters and per-definition permission scope. These invariants are enforced in the use case rather than only at the edge, so the same rules hold for every caller.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:configurationregistryandhistorysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistoryerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistoryerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Outcomes are deterministic and fail-closed: invalid input maps to a validation error, unknown keys to not-found, non-overridable definitions to an unprocessable-entity outcome, insufficient permission to forbidden, and absence of tenant context to a bad-request; successful writes and deletes return no-content. Best-effort change-notification fan-out is decoupled and its failure never rolls back the committed configuration mutation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:configurationregistryandhistorysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistoryauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistoryauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "A set operation emits the definition's configured change audit action and a clear operation emits a value-cleared audit action, in both cases before the tenant settings are mutated and carrying key and value metadata. Audit emission is a precondition for the write, so a failed audit prevents the persistence change entirely.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:configurationregistryandhistorysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistoryreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistoryreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The capability is invariant-ready once the tenant settings store is reachable; the definition registry itself is pure and serialisable and therefore always available, while the history/audit projection of past changes is validated separately. When the persistence substrate is unavailable the capability degrades explicitly rather than silently serving stale or partial values.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:configurationregistryandhistorysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistoryproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistoryproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by unit proofs over the configuration use case and contract validation (definition resolution, override source, validation rules, and audit-first writes) and by an adjacent live history projection proof that validates the audit/history record of configuration changes against a real substrate. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:configurationregistryandhistorysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistoryuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:configurationregistryandhistoryuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The configurationregistryandhistory capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:configurationregistryandhistory> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
