<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracte2econfidenceladderstageaware> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracte2econfidenceladderstageaware";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/e2econfidenceladderstageaware.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracte2econfidenceladderstageaware>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracte2econfidenceladderstageaware> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracte2econfidenceladderstageaware";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/e2econfidenceladderstageaware.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:e2econfidenceladderstageawaresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracte2econfidenceladderstageaware>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracte2econfidenceladderstageaware>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracte2econfidenceladderstageaware>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawarelifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawarelifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Gate/governance capability that defines a stage-aware end-to-end confidence ladder gating promotion across hermetic, integration, staging, and production-shaped stages without upgrading proof posture by implication; it is neither provider-backed nor database-backed. It deploys the V1-proven e2e registries-plus-validators contract and must keep its lifecycle/readiness model unchanged during extraction, with migrations limited to contract/config references. Recovery re-runs the verify-ladder and aggregate-confidence tests before promotion continues.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:e2econfidenceladderstageawaresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawarestatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawarestatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The state is the ladder definition and the aggregated confidence over its stages: the registry of e2e journeys, their required stages, and the per-stage pass/fail roll-up, held as configuration and evidence rather than owned tenant rows. It has no owned database schema, so backup scope is configuration/evidence only and restore cannot create tenant data. Each stage's posture is tracked independently so a higher stage cannot inherit a lower stage's proof.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:e2econfidenceladderstageawaresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawarepermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawarepermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The ladder owns no tenant data and exposes no tenant-mutating routes, so standard platform security controls apply; its effect on tenants is indirect via promotion gating. Configuring the ladder and its stages is an operator/governance concern, not an end-user permission. It reads e2e results rather than mutating service state.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:e2econfidenceladderstageawaresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawarecontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawarecontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract is the e2e registries plus the validators that decide whether a stage's confidence threshold is met, defining what each stage requires to pass. Configuration is read from the declared provider/config plane and missing or invalid configuration fails closed instead of inventing defaults. The per-stage gate is the contract that promotion decisions consume.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:e2econfidenceladderstageawaresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawarevalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawarevalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Validation enforces that each stage's required journeys ran and passed and that confidence is aggregated honestly, never letting a hermetic pass stand in for an integration, staging, or production-shaped pass. Inputs are the e2e results per stage, which must be present and current. Missing, stale, or unknown stage results are treated as not-pass.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:e2econfidenceladderstageawaresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawareerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawareerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Local failure returns a typed platform error or a readiness-degraded state without changing tenant-visible semantics; there is no external provider to fabricate, so unavailable local dependencies fail closed through the readiness model. The risk class is semantic drift or configuration loss, not tenant data loss. A blocked ladder readiness or a failing promotion gate is an alertable foundation condition.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:e2econfidenceladderstageawaresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawareauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawareauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Because it performs no tenant mutation, its audit concern is the integrity of the confidence record: the per-stage results and the aggregated verdict are observable evidence that promotion decisions can be traced to. Readiness and the ladder verdict remain visible in degraded mode. Recovery re-runs the verify-ladder and aggregate-confidence tests so the verdict stays evidence-backed.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:e2econfidenceladderstageawaresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawarereadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawarereadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is the stage-aware verdict itself: a capability may advance only when its current stage's confidence threshold is met, and the ladder degrades explicitly rather than upgrading posture by implication. It fails closed on missing, stale, or unknown stage evidence. Promotion is gated on the verify-ladder and aggregate-confidence checks passing.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:e2econfidenceladderstageawaresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawareproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawareproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Proof is the verify-ladder and aggregate-confidence test suites that demonstrate the ladder gates promotion per stage without inflating proof posture. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:e2econfidenceladderstageawaresemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawareuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:e2econfidenceladderstageawareuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The e2econfidenceladderstageaware capability is explicitly internal; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:e2econfidenceladderstageaware> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicesemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicesemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:scc0b8959542e483604656bc9821a18062b0c9af00552fddb8cb5ba86dbc76345>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "3bc7ad5e4498e9eb43c096086b5d2efdaf7fb49f68ad8e2a439469a897ab8fcb";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/end-user-profile-and-preferences-self-service.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractenduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractenduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractenduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractenduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractenduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractenduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractenduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractenduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractenduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractenduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractenduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractenduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicelifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicelifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Profile lifecycle moves from a default to an updated own-profile record, and preference lifecycle moves from default-empty to updated channel/category preferences that are read back; notification dispatch then treats enabled preferences as sent and disabled preferences as suppressed. All operations act only on the authenticated subject's own data.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicestatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicestatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State is tenant-and-user-scoped: a profile (display name, locale, timezone), a preference set (channel, category, enabled flag), and a durable dispatch log status of sent, suppressed, or failed. There are no secret-bearing columns in the self-service state.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicepermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicepermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Reads use a self-read permission and writes use a self-update permission, with the user id always taken from the authenticated session subject and never from a path or body parameter. The separate operator notification test uses platform notification permissions outside this self-service surface, preserving isolation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicecontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicecontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The operation surface is read and update of the caller's own profile and notification preferences, with supporting notification readiness and test operations. Responses return the updated record or a typed validation result.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicevalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicevalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Profile update rejects an empty display name, the route schema rejects invalid profile or preference payloads, dispatch rejects secret-bearing payload fields, and a write without tenant context returns a no-tenant error. Invalid input is rejected before any change.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfserviceerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfserviceerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Validation failures return safe validation-error responses, no-tenant writes return a 400 no-tenant outcome, and secret-bearing notification payloads raise an explicit not-notifiable error; provider failure returns a typed degraded result fail-closed. No partial profile state is persisted on failure.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfserviceauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfserviceauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Profile updates emit a profile-updated audit-before-change event, preference updates emit a preference audit, and operator test sends emit a notification-tested event. Audit precedes the change.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicereadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicereadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Profile and preferences are always-on once the data substrate is migrated, and degraded mode disables store-dependent writes while keeping read-only access and audit visible. Live proofs skip honestly when the substrate is unavailable and verify no secret columns plus tenant-isolation enforcement.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfserviceproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfserviceproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Unit proofs cover the profile and notification usecases, and runtime proofs validate live profile self-service, notification preferences, and dispatch against the data substrate with row-level tenant isolation, demonstrated in source lineage via hermetic/runtime validation. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservicesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfserviceuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfserviceuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice capability has one framework-neutral UI semantic model with explicit surfaces, view models, components, journeys, permissions, accessibility, localisation, and target-specific renderer contracts. This semantic closure disclaims product parity, human acceptance, accessibility compliance, and launch-language readiness.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:enduserprofileandpreferencesselfservice> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:entitlementenginesemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "entitlementenginesemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:sc8adc11e1c53c66e8f9c543bba8fc5d6a77d1c2af14d1974f9eb87f83641c1da>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:entitlementengine>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "8531489e92dfaed34850b6b508a71120d44aa0bbb9ade37af4ea13e067dcdb40";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/entitlement-engine.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:entitlementengine> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractentitlementengine>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractentitlementengine> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractentitlementengine";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractentitlementengine>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:entitlementengine>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractentitlementengine> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractentitlementengine";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/entitlementengine.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractentitlementengine>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractentitlementengine> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractentitlementengine";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/entitlementengine.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:entitlementenginesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractentitlementengine>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractentitlementengine>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractentitlementengine>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementenginelifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementenginelifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Entitlement lifecycle is deny-by-default: an absent or not-granted key denies, an operator grant moves a key to granted, an operator revoke moves it to revoked, and both revoked and absent block access. Tenant self-reads project the catalog of keys as granted, revoked, or not-granted.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:entitlementenginesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementenginestatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementenginestatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State is an organisation id plus entitlement key with a state of granted or revoked alongside source, metadata, update timestamp, and updater, while the tenant self-read view projects every catalog key into granted, revoked, or not-granted. Feature flags are explicitly distinct from entitlements.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:entitlementenginesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementenginepermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementenginepermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Tenant read requires the tenant entitlements read permission and operator read/write require the platform entitlements read/write permissions, and policy-chain evaluation denies on missing permission before evaluating entitlement. Cross-tenant grants do not leak across the tenant boundary.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:entitlementenginesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementenginecontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementenginecontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The operation surface is a tenant self-read of entitlements, an operator read of a tenant's entitlements, an operator write to grant or revoke, and a service-catalog read. Decisions are enforced through an assert/evaluate seam rather than only returned data.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:entitlementenginesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementenginevalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementenginevalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Unknown entitlement keys are rejected without audit, invalid tenant identifiers return 400, feature flags are not treated as entitlements, and cross-tenant grants do not leak. Invalid input changes no state.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:entitlementenginesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementengineerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementengineerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The assertion path throws a typed forbidden error when not entitled, the evaluation path returns a denied decision by permission or entitlement, and invalid tenant or key cases return 400; provider failure returns a typed degraded result fail-closed. Access defaults to denied when state is missing.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:entitlementenginesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementengineauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementengineauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Grant and revoke emit entitlement-granted and entitlement-revoked audit-before-change events, and a failing audit blocks persistence and leaves rows unchanged. Read-side evaluation is not audited as a mutation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:entitlementenginesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementenginereadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementenginereadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Entitlement reads are deterministic once the data substrate is migrated, and degraded mode disables store-dependent mutation while keeping read-only reads and audit visible. Live readiness verifies table existence, forced row-level security, no secret columns, tenant isolation, operator bypass, grant/revoke, and audit-before-change.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:entitlementenginesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementengineproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementengineproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "A unit proof covers the deny-by-default state machine and runtime proofs cover the entitlement seam, permission-before-entitlement ordering, the live data substrate, and the routes, demonstrated in source lineage via hermetic and live-substrate validation. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:entitlementenginesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementengineuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:entitlementengineuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The entitlementengine capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:entitlementengine> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
