<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractenvironmentspecificvssharedservicemodel> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractenvironmentspecificvssharedservicemodel";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/environmentspecificvssharedservicemodel.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractenvironmentspecificvssharedservicemodel>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractenvironmentspecificvssharedservicemodel> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractenvironmentspecificvssharedservicemodel";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/environmentspecificvssharedservicemodel.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractenvironmentspecificvssharedservicemodel>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractenvironmentspecificvssharedservicemodel>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractenvironmentspecificvssharedservicemodel>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodellifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodellifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Classification model that decides whether each service is environment-specific or shared and governs the routing and isolation that follows; it is provider-backed but owns no database schema. It deploys a classification contract (V1 contract n/a) and must keep its lifecycle/readiness model unchanged during extraction, with migrations limited to contract/config references that must update semantic artefacts when behaviour changes. Rollback restores the previous classification implementation and re-runs the named proof evidence.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The state is the per-service classification (environment-specific vs shared) and the routing/isolation rules derived from it, held as configuration rather than owned tenant rows. It has no owned database schema, so backup scope is configuration/evidence only and restore cannot create tenant data. Classification changes propagate to how services are resolved per environment.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "It owns no tenant records and exposes no tenant-mutating routes, so standard platform security controls apply; its tenant impact is indirect through the isolation it enforces. The classification determines whether a service instance is shared across environments or isolated to one, which is an operator/governance concern rather than an end-user permission. Correct classification is what keeps environment boundaries from leaking.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract is the classification decision and the routing/isolation guarantees it implies for consumers, mediated through the configuration plane rather than a tenant API. Configuration is read from the declared provider/config plane and missing or invalid configuration fails closed instead of inventing defaults. Consumers rely on the classification to know whether a dependency is environment-specific or shared.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Validation ensures every relevant service has an explicit, consistent classification and that shared-versus-specific assignments do not violate environment isolation. Drift or configuration loss is the failure to guard against. Misclassification that would cross an environment boundary is rejected.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Provider failure returns a typed degraded/readiness failure, keeps mutation boundaries closed, and does not fabricate successful provider state; degraded mode disables dependent side-effect paths while keeping read-only readiness and audit visible. The risk class is semantic drift or configuration loss, not tenant data loss. Blocked readiness or a failing promotion proof is alertable.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Because it owns no tenant mutations, its audit concern is the recorded classification lineage: changes to whether a service is shared or environment-specific are captured as reviewable configuration/semantic changes. Readiness and audit remain visible in degraded mode. This preserves an honest record of isolation decisions.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness means every service's environment classification is present, consistent, and enforced, and the routing/isolation it implies resolves; unavailable dependencies fail closed through the readiness model. Readiness is shown by re-running the environment-service-classification document and named proof. Stale or unknown classifications do not count as ready.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Proof is the environment-service-classification document and associated checks demonstrating consistent shared-versus-environment-specific classification; it is a foundation-document proof rather than a live runtime probe. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodeluisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodeluisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The environmentspecificvssharedservicemodel capability is explicitly internal; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:environmentspecificvssharedservicemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
