    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracteventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrive> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracteventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrive";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrive.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracteventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrive>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracteventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrive>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracteventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrive>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivelifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivelifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The capability publishes a pending event, deduplicates it by organisation, event type, and caller-supplied idempotency key, lets a worker claim and process it to processed, retries a failing handler with bounded backoff up to maxAttempts, then transitions the record to dead_letter; an operator redrive re-enqueues a dead-lettered event as a fresh pending event under a new idempotency key. Canonical product events carry strict, versioned payload contracts (for example tenant.config.changed keyed on key and report.run keyed on reportId) while the generic event-bus path also backs test-only fixture events excluded from product readiness. Provider failure degrades readiness rather than fabricating successful delivery.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivestatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivestatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Persistent state is the platform_events table partitioned by organisationId, holding eventType, idempotencyKey, payload, status in pending|processing|processed|dead_letter, and attempts against maxAttempts, alongside worker_heartbeats recording alive|stale|stopped liveness. Dead-letter records retain tenant, event type, attempt count, a payload summary, and the last error so redrive can reconstruct context; ordering is guaranteed per organisation and idempotency key with no cross-tenant ordering guarantee. Row-level security scopes every read and mutation to the owning organisation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivepermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivepermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Routes are global, operator-only platform surfaces: reading the event list and the dead-letter list requires platform.events.read, redrive requires platform.events.write, and worker listing requires platform.workers.read. Tenant isolation is enforced by organisationId partitioning plus row-level security so one organisation can never observe or redrive another organisation's events, and list routes require an explicit organisationId. Secrets and provider credentials never cross the event boundary.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivecontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivecontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The external operator contract is GET /api/admin/events, GET /api/admin/events/dead-letter, and POST /api/admin/events/:eventId/redrive, with publishing and worker processing exposed only as server-internal use-case contracts behind the EventBusPort and its PostgresEventBusAdapter. Schema changes to canonical events require a new schemaVersion, backwards-compatible consumers, and migration/redrive compatibility evidence before promotion. The port/adapter seam keeps the persistence provider swappable without changing the operation semantics.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivevalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivevalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Publish rejects payload fields that carry secrets, preserves the tenant id, and deduplicates repeated idempotency keys; list routes require organisationId and return 400 when it is missing, and redrive rejects an invalid or unknown event id with 400. Row-level security additionally hides foreign-tenant events so validation cannot be bypassed by id guessing. Invariants are exercised by the event-bus and event-redrive runtime proofs.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredriveerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredriveerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Outcomes are deterministic and fail closed: a duplicate publish is deduplicated, a handler that exhausts maxAttempts is dead-lettered, a missing organisationId returns 400, an invalid redrive id returns 400, and an unavailable Postgres substrate yields an honest skip or readiness failure rather than a fabricated success. Errors are typed and logged with organisationId when tenant-scoped, and no failure path echoes secret-bearing payload fields.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredriveauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredriveauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Operator redrive emits an event.redriven audit record under audit-before-change semantics, so the audit write precedes the state mutation. Event publication and worker processing are captured as durable operational records and worker heartbeats rather than as user-mutation audit events, and redrive audit excludes the underlying payload. This separation keeps the operational telemetry distinct from the privileged-action audit trail.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivereadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivereadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness combines operator visibility of the event and dead-letter queues with worker heartbeat liveness (alive|stale|stopped); it degrades explicitly and disables mutation/side-effect paths that depend on the Postgres adapter while keeping read-only readiness and audit visible. Live proofs fail closed on row-level-security, secret-payload, retry, redrive, or heartbeat regressions and skip honestly when Postgres is unavailable, so production-shaped readiness is never reported as production-live.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredriveproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredriveproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by three runtime proofs: event-bus validates live Postgres outbox persistence, row-level security, and secret-payload rejection; event-worker validates processing, retry, dead-letter, and heartbeat; event-redrive validates the live admin routes and requeue, with the corpus describing this as level-4 live substrate and route validation. The proofs are the lineage evidence, not a USF readiness claim. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrivesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredriveuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredriveuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrive capability is explicitly internal; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:eventbusdurablequeuesdlqredrive> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionsemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionsemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:s717a4196386fca43cfc09361ff4e435af40f29129d30f82a137401cc9414af48>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "2f93c3a7e0601376e34b970069195582c12e3a061150e02187fb1111a8933a6e";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/history-read-model-read-only-projection.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojection> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracthistoryreadmodelreadonlyprojection>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracthistoryreadmodelreadonlyprojection> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracthistoryreadmodelreadonlyprojection";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracthistoryreadmodelreadonlyprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojection>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracthistoryreadmodelreadonlyprojection> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracthistoryreadmodelreadonlyprojection";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/historyreadmodelreadonlyprojection.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracthistoryreadmodelreadonlyprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracthistoryreadmodelreadonlyprojection> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracthistoryreadmodelreadonlyprojection";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/historyreadmodelreadonlyprojection.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracthistoryreadmodelreadonlyprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracthistoryreadmodelreadonlyprojection>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracthistoryreadmodelreadonlyprojection>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionlifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionlifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Provides a read-only projection of tenant and admin history assembled from audit and related sources, exposed through tenant-history and admin-tenant-history reads; it is strictly a query surface and performs no mutation. Entries are projected from underlying records into a safe summarised shape on read. The projection deliberately excludes sensitive raw material so history can be browsed without exposing secrets.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Each history entry carries an identifier, source, type, title, occurrence time, and a safe actor/status summary, returned with total, limit, and offset for paging; it deliberately excludes raw metadata, payloads, tokens, and secrets. The model is a projection over existing audit and event records rather than an owned canonical table, served through a history repository port. Paging fields make the read-only result set bounded and navigable.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Reads are tenant-scoped so a tenant sees only its own history, while the admin variant is operator-scoped to read a named tenant's history under privileged access; both preserve tenant isolation. Because the projection omits payloads, tokens, and secrets, even authorised readers cannot extract sensitive material through history. Access flows through ports and adapters, never a direct client database connection.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectioncontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectioncontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract is two read operations (tenant history and admin tenant history) returning the paged, summarised projection shape with no write side. The repository port defines the query and paging contract, and the projection guarantees the exclusion of raw payloads and secrets as a contract obligation. As a read-only surface it participates in backup/export/retention semantics only as a consumer of the underlying records.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Paging inputs (limit, offset) are validated and bounded, and the projection enforces the safe-shape contract by emitting only the allowed summary fields. Tenant context is required so the read is correctly scoped. Missing or invalid configuration fails closed rather than returning an unscoped result.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Because it is read-only there is no mutation to roll back; failures return a typed degraded or readiness error rather than a partial or fabricated result, and the read fails closed when tenant context or the substrate is unavailable. Provider failure keeps boundaries closed and does not invent history entries. Tenant data cannot be exposed across tenants.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The capability is itself a window onto the audit/history record set, presenting a safe summarised view; reads preserve tenant context through spans and typed logs carry the tenant/organisation identifier when tenant-scoped. It never writes, so it adds no mutation audit of its own beyond the access trail. The underlying audit records it projects remain the canonical evidence.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness depends on the underlying audit/history store being reachable; the capability degrades explicitly when that substrate is unavailable, keeping read-only readiness and audit visible (it has no mutation path to disable). Readiness being blocked, a failed history proof during promotion, or a missing isolation or audit signal raise alerts and block promotion.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by the history proof against the history repository projection, asserting the safe summarised shape and tenant scoping. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojectionuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The historyreadmodelreadonlyprojection capability is explicitly internal; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:historyreadmodelreadonlyprojection> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:i18nruntimeandvalidationsemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "i18nruntimeandvalidationsemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:s12502805027b73209f328094c68746b4d83ec795c7cab02d164b6eadda227220>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:i18nruntimeandvalidation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "b43bbb1160beea1b2f1c23f2c79cfde9d374c1428d7e96b4cff14a902fbe1a5b";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/i18n-runtime-and-validation.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:i18nruntimeandvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracti18nruntimeandvalidation>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracti18nruntimeandvalidation> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracti18nruntimeandvalidation";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracti18nruntimeandvalidation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:i18nruntimeandvalidation>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracti18nruntimeandvalidation> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracti18nruntimeandvalidation";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/i18nruntimeandvalidation.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracti18nruntimeandvalidation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracti18nruntimeandvalidation> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracti18nruntimeandvalidation";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/i18nruntimeandvalidation.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:i18nruntimeandvalidationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracti18nruntimeandvalidation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracti18nruntimeandvalidation>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracti18nruntimeandvalidation>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationlifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationlifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Provides runtime internationalisation with locale resolution plus a validation gate that ensures required keys exist and raw literals are governed, treating UI strings as contractual; it is database-backed in lineage but owns no tenant records. It deploys the V1-proven packages/i18n-runtime contract and must keep its lifecycle/readiness model unchanged during extraction, with the validation gate run as a build/promotion check. Recovery re-runs the i18n-runtime package and its validation before promotion continues.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:i18nruntimeandvalidationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State includes the flattened locale key map, the duplicate list, the used-key set, interpolation parameter usage, raw-literal findings, governed/exclude/exception configuration, the strictFailOnRawLiteral flag, and the strict/report-only exit state. Database changes use ordered migrations that must preserve this proven model. The state is the validation corpus over translation keys rather than owned tenant data.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:i18nruntimeandvalidationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The i18n runtime and its validation own no tenant data and expose no tenant-mutating routes, so standard platform security controls apply; the gate is an operator/CI concern rather than an end-user permission. Locale resolution serves all users and is not tenant-gated. Governing which literals are exempt is a configuration authority, not an end-user role.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:i18nruntimeandvalidationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract has two faces: the runtime locale-resolution interface that resolves keys to strings for a locale, and the validation interface that asserts required keys exist, no raw literals leak, and interpolation parameters match. Configuration is read from the declared provider/config plane and missing or invalid configuration fails closed instead of inventing defaults. UI strings are contractual, so missing keys are a contract violation rather than a soft fallback.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:i18nruntimeandvalidationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Validation checks for missing required keys, duplicate keys, unused keys, mismatched interpolation parameters, and ungoverned raw literals, honouring the governed/exclude/exception configuration. In strict mode (strictFailOnRawLiteral) it fails closed and returns a non-zero exit; in report-only mode it surfaces findings without blocking. The used-key set is reconciled against the locale key map so drift is caught at gate time.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:i18nruntimeandvalidationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Local failure returns a typed platform error or a readiness-degraded state without changing tenant-visible semantics; unavailable local dependencies fail closed through the readiness model. In strict mode a missing key or ungoverned raw literal produces a failing exit state rather than a silent default. The risk class is semantic drift or configuration loss, not tenant data loss.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:i18nruntimeandvalidationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Because it performs no tenant mutation, its audit concern is the validation record: the duplicate list, raw-literal findings, and strict/report-only exit state form the reviewable evidence of i18n conformance. These findings remain visible so locale governance is inspectable. Recovery re-runs the validation so the conformance claim stays evidence-backed.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:i18nruntimeandvalidationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness means the locale corpus passes the validation gate (required keys present, interpolation consistent, raw literals governed) for the configured strictness; unavailable dependencies fail closed through the readiness model. Readiness is demonstrated by re-running validate-i18n and the i18n-runtime tests. A report-only pass with outstanding strict findings is not full readiness.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:i18nruntimeandvalidationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by validate-i18n and the i18n-runtime tests, demonstrating locale resolution and the key/raw-literal/interpolation validation gate. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:i18nruntimeandvalidationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:i18nruntimeandvalidationuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The i18nruntimeandvalidation capability is explicitly internal; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:i18nruntimeandvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:internalservicecatalogandreadinesssemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
