    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:internalservicecatalogandreadiness>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractinternalservicecatalogandreadiness> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractinternalservicecatalogandreadiness";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/internalservicecatalogandreadiness.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractinternalservicecatalogandreadiness>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractinternalservicecatalogandreadiness> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractinternalservicecatalogandreadiness";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/internalservicecatalogandreadiness.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:internalservicecatalogandreadinesssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractinternalservicecatalogandreadiness>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractinternalservicecatalogandreadiness>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractinternalservicecatalogandreadiness>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinesslifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinesslifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Maintains an internal catalog of platform services and aggregates their readiness probes into a single tenant-scoped platform services readiness contract, so operators and tenant admins can see which composed services are ready. The capability is provider-backed and tenant-aware; it must keep its lifecycle/readiness model stable across extraction and preserve tenant isolation on what each tenant can observe.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:internalservicecatalogandreadinesssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinessstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinessstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "It owns no database schema of its own: service descriptors and readiness come from the catalog and from per-service readiness probes accessed through a readiness-probe port, with the capability holding a derived, tenant-scoped readiness record. Probe results are aggregated into discrete ready/degraded/blocked states per service, and behaviour changes update semantic artefacts rather than introducing owned tenant rows.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:internalservicecatalogandreadinesssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinesspermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinesspermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Catalog and readiness reads are scoped to the caller's tenant so a tenant sees only the services and readiness it is entitled to, with standard platform security controls applied. Because the readiness view can expose tenant-visible posture, isolation must be preserved and unscoped access fails closed rather than revealing other tenants' service state.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:internalservicecatalogandreadinesssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinesscontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinesscontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Exposes a tenant-scoped platform services readiness query backed by a provider readiness-probe port, so individual service health checks are swappable without changing the catalog contract. The aggregate response has a stable shape (per-service identity plus readiness state) and composes with the composed-provider readiness spine for end-to-end readiness reporting.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:internalservicecatalogandreadinesssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinessvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinessvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Requests are validated for required tenant scope and well-formed service references before probes are invoked, and missing or invalid configuration fails closed instead of inventing default readiness. Aggregation invariants ensure a service with an unknown or failed probe is reported as not-ready rather than silently omitted.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:internalservicecatalogandreadinesssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinesserrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinesserrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "A failing or unavailable readiness probe yields a typed degraded/readiness failure for that service and never fabricates a ready state; mutation boundaries stay closed and the aggregate reflects the worst-case truth. Tenant data loss is possible only if backup/restore/export semantics are bypassed, so recovery preserves the tenant boundary and audit lineage.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:internalservicecatalogandreadinesssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinessauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinessauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness queries and catalog interactions are correlated to request and trace identifiers, and any state-affecting catalog action is recorded as an auditable event preserving tenant boundary and DSR/GDPR evidence. A missing tenant-isolation or audit signal on this surface is itself an alert condition.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:internalservicecatalogandreadinesssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinessreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinessreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is the capability's primary output: it aggregates per-service probes into a tenant-scoped posture that degrades explicitly when a probe, provider, or substrate is unavailable, keeping read-only readiness and audit visible while disabling dependent side-effect paths. Emitted readiness, error, and audit signals use the controlled, OpenTelemetry-informed observability vocabulary.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:internalservicecatalogandreadinesssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinessproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinessproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by the cited platform-services and service-catalog-registry runtime proofs (and the composed-provider readiness proof), demonstrating catalog aggregation and tenant-scoped readiness reporting as hermetic/runtime lineage rather than a current-readiness claim. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:internalservicecatalogandreadinesssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinessuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:internalservicecatalogandreadinessuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The internalservicecatalogandreadiness capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:internalservicecatalogandreadiness> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchsemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchsemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:s5ab9ad99c3138be826c7ec952db20f9bae996aaa13914b80f1471d071cd3003f>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "af26ff637904731bddbe793af3533697d1788e922aa53bf08bc9d642f0635113";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/logs-aggregation-and-tenant-scoped-search.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractlogsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractlogsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractlogsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractlogsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractlogsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractlogsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractlogsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractlogsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractlogsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractlogsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractlogsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractlogsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchlifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchlifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Aggregates application and audit logs into a queryable log store and exposes a tenant-scoped search contract (log search plus an observability readiness query) that admins use to investigate behaviour within a single tenant boundary. The capability is provider-backed and tenant-data-owning, so the lifecycle/readiness model must be preserved unchanged across extraction and every search request carries and enforces the tenant context.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Persisted state is log entries keyed by low-cardinality service and level labels, with high-cardinality identifiers (organisation/tenant id, request id, trace id) carried as structured fields rather than labels to control series cardinality. Backing the entries is a readiness record exposing the discrete states log ingestion, tenant-scoped query, trace correlation, dashboards, collector, metrics, and error capture; schema evolution uses ordered, forward-only migrations that preserve tenant rows and audit lineage.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Search and readiness operations are admin-gated and hard-bound to a single tenant: every query is scoped to the caller's organisation id so one tenant can never read another tenant's log entries. Permission, audit, and fail-closed checks are treated as security-sensitive invariants that must survive extraction unchanged, and missing tenant context fails the request rather than widening scope.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Exposes a tenant-scoped log search operation and an observability readiness query behind ports/adapters, so the log-store provider (e.g. a Loki-style backend) is swappable without changing the contract surface. Inputs are validated and normalised before reaching the adapter, and the response shape (matched entries plus readiness state) is stable so callers and dashboards depend on semantics, not provider internals.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Search inputs (time range, label/field filters, tenant scope) are validated for type and bounds before execution, and the mandatory tenant scope is asserted so an unscoped or cross-tenant query is rejected rather than broadened. Invariants are enforced ahead of any provider call so malformed input cannot reach the log store or leak entries outside the tenant boundary.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearcherrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearcherrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Errors are deterministic and fail-closed: a provider or substrate failure returns a typed degraded/readiness failure instead of fabricating successful provider state or empty-but-authoritative results. Error logs carry the organisation id when tenant-scoped, mutation and side-effect paths stay closed under failure, and no partial result is presented as complete.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State-changing and security-relevant actions emit audit records before the effect is acknowledged, so the audit trail cannot diverge from what actually happened. Audit entries preserve tenant boundary, request/trace correlation, and DSR/GDPR evidence requirements, and a missing tenant-isolation or audit signal is itself an alertable condition.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is a first-class, queryable posture reporting the discrete sub-states (log ingestion, tenant-scoped query, trace correlation, dashboards, collector, metrics, error capture) and degrades explicitly when the search adapter or substrate is unavailable. In degraded mode mutation/side-effect paths that depend on the search adapter are disabled while read-only readiness and audit visibility are retained; emitted readiness, error, and audit signals use the controlled, OpenTelemetry-informed observability vocabulary.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by the cited tenant-observability runtime proof plus logs use-case tests, demonstrating tenant-scoped search, readiness reporting, and fail-closed isolation as hermetic/runtime lineage rather than a current-readiness claim. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearchuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:logsaggregationandtenantscopedsearch> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:metricsandtracessemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
