<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractpitrretentionlegalholddataresidency> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractpitrretentionlegalholddataresidency";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/pitrretentionlegalholddataresidency.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractpitrretentionlegalholddataresidency>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractpitrretentionlegalholddataresidency> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractpitrretentionlegalholddataresidency";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/pitrretentionlegalholddataresidency.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractpitrretentionlegalholddataresidency>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractpitrretentionlegalholddataresidency>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractpitrretentionlegalholddataresidency>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencylifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencylifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Provides point-in-time recovery drills, per-resource retention windows, legal holds that block deletion, and single-region data-residency tagging over tenant data, exposed through administrative data operations. A retention worker periodically evaluates expired candidates and deletes or anonymises them UNLESS an active legal hold protects the resource; legal holds move from active to released and residency tags are owned on the tenant record. The whole capability fails closed where source data or configuration is unavailable so that retention never destroys protected or unverified data.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencystatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencystatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Retention policies are tenant-scoped rows naming a target resource class, a time-to-live window, an apply filter (all rows or by status), and an enabled flag; each retention candidate resolves to an outcome of pending, deleted, or held. Legal holds are tenant-scoped records with active or released state plus reason, set-by and released-by actors, and set and released timestamps, where active is defined by an unset release timestamp; the held-row invariant is that an active hold on a resource blocks its retention deletion. Data residency is a single-region tag owned by the tenant/organisation row, and placement enforcement rejects writes targeting a non-home region.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencypermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencypermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "All four sub-capabilities are tenant-scoped under the canonical row-level-security predicate (tenant isolation plus the dedicated bypass role), so one tenant cannot see or affect another tenant's retention policies, holds, or residency. Setting or releasing a legal hold and managing retention policies are privileged operations attributed to an actor; residency placement is enforced fail-closed against the tenant's home region. The retention worker operates under a system-admin/bypass context to evaluate candidates across the tenant's protected tables.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencycontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencycontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The capability exposes administrative operations for point-in-time recovery, retention policies, legal holds, and residency. The retention contract guarantees that a hold-guarded resource is never deleted by the retention tick, the legal-hold contract guarantees deletion is blocked while a hold is active, and the residency contract guarantees writes to a non-home region are rejected. Recovery must preserve tenant boundary, audit, and data-subject evidence.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencyvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencyvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Retention evaluation validates the configured window and filter and, critically, checks for an active legal hold before treating any candidate as deletable. Legal-hold operations validate actor and reason; residency placement validates the target region against the tenant's home tag and rejects mismatches. Point-in-time recovery is validated by a restore drill rather than assumed.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencyerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencyerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The model is fail-closed and safety-sensitive: when source data, configuration, or hold state is unavailable, retention does not delete, residency rejects out-of-region writes, and provider failure returns a typed degraded or readiness error with mutation boundaries closed. Tenant data cannot be silently dropped or remapped; an unverified hold or window leaves the candidate in the pending or held outcome rather than deleted. Incident class is tenant-data-or-security with explicit tenant-data-loss risk if retention or restore semantics are bypassed.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencyauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencyauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Legal holds capture set-by and released-by actors with reason and lifecycle timestamps, providing a durable record of who protected what and why. Retention outcomes (pending, deleted, held) and residency rejections are observable per tenant through tenant-scoped error logs and route/use-case/provider spans that preserve tenant context. Recovery and restore must preserve audit and data-subject evidence alongside the data.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencyreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencyreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is gated on the retention worker, legal-hold store, and residency enforcement being reachable and on the restore drill succeeding; the capability degrades explicitly when its adapters or the residency column are unavailable, keeping read-only readiness and audit visible while disabling the deletion path. Readiness being blocked, a failed restore/retention/legal-hold/residency proof during promotion, or a missing isolation or audit signal raise alerts and block promotion.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencyproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencyproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by point-in-time restore-drill, retention, legal-hold, and data-residency proofs, including the retention tick worker proven to honour active holds. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencyuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidencyuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The pitrretentionlegalholddataresidency capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:pitrretentionlegalholddataresidency> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:productcatalogplanspricessemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "productcatalogplanspricessemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:sbb3817290bd4f86f32469882ede5ef307c8f5f6d6bc16aa09ef0e1c42356d40d>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:productcatalogplansprices>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "33b15e0265b918b7fc545939642ff06660dd4fb72dcc7ae9a019ce4e326e3c2c";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/product-catalog-plans-prices.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:productcatalogplansprices> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractproductcatalogplansprices>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractproductcatalogplansprices> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractproductcatalogplansprices";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractproductcatalogplansprices>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:productcatalogplansprices>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractproductcatalogplansprices> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractproductcatalogplansprices";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/productcatalogplansprices.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractproductcatalogplansprices>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractproductcatalogplansprices> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractproductcatalogplansprices";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/productcatalogplansprices.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:productcatalogplanspricessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractproductcatalogplansprices>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractproductcatalogplansprices>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractproductcatalogplansprices>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspriceslifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspriceslifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The catalog lifecycle creates and lists products, then plans optionally filtered by product, then prices optionally filtered by plan, while tenant reads return the combined active catalog view. All write paths are operator-scoped and the in-house catalog is treated as the semantic source of truth for billable products, plans, and prices. Catalog mutations carry actor identity into the use-case layer so changes are attributable.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:productcatalogplanspricessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricesstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricesstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State is a three-level hierarchy: Product (identifier, name, description, active flag, created timestamp), Plan (identifier, owning product, name, currency, billing period, active flag, created timestamp), and Price (identifier, owning plan, version, price type, unit amount, currency, billing period, active flag, created timestamp). Items carry explicit active/inactive state rather than being hard-deleted, and price versioning preserves historical amounts. State changes flow through ordered migrations that must preserve this proven model.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:productcatalogplanspricessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricespermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricespermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Operator catalog list and create operations require platform billing administration permission with read/write authorization; tenant catalog reads require a tenant billing-read permission and are scoped to the requesting organisation. Permission and entitlement checks run before any adapter call, and tenant context cannot read or mutate another tenant's catalog view.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:productcatalogplanspricessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricescontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricescontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract surface exposes operator create/list operations for products, plans, and prices plus a combined tenant catalog read, with plan and price list operations accepting product/plan filter parameters. Create payloads conform to per-entity request schemas, and the interface is mediated by a catalog port with a relational adapter so callers never bind to storage directly.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:productcatalogplanspricessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricesvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricesvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Create bodies are validated against product, plan, and price request schemas before any persistence call, rejecting malformed input with a typed validation outcome up front. Currency, billing-period, price-type, and amount fields are explicitly typed, and references between price, plan, and product must resolve.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:productcatalogplanspricessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspriceserrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspriceserrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Invalid create bodies fail closed with a validation error and permission denials are returned before handlers execute, so no partial catalog write occurs. Successful creates return the created entity with a creation status while list operations return the current set; provider failure degrades to a typed readiness failure rather than fabricating catalog state.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:productcatalogplanspricessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricesauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricesauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Catalog mutations record a catalog-changed audit action carrying the acting operator identity into the use-case and adapter layers, so every product/plan/price change is attributable. Route-registration proof is explicitly not treated as an audit proof; audit is a distinct, mutation-bound record.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:productcatalogplanspricessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricesreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricesreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is migration- and catalog-seed-backed: route-registration evidence validates the exposed surface and unit behaviour validates in-process catalog operations, while live provider billing readiness is tracked as a separate capability. When the catalog adapter is unavailable, mutation paths are disabled and only read-only readiness and audit remain visible.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:productcatalogplanspricessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricesproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricesproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by catalog unit tests and a catalog route-registration runtime proof, with live HTTP-backed plan synchronisation validated separately through the external billing provider adapter. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:productcatalogplanspricessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricesuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:productcatalogplanspricesuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The productcatalogplansprices capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:productcatalogplansprices> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerconfigurationplanesemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "providerconfigurationplanesemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:s835e433b2c6ea1e00b868b1dfddbcae1d7c67d4fffa9b38c91932199be733ad9>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:providerconfigurationplane>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "cb2432289569d594dfe66b16325a799d8b3b545ab7b9157e1d0d88cd34edde74";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/provider-configuration-plane.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:providerconfigurationplane> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractproviderconfigurationplane>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractproviderconfigurationplane> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractproviderconfigurationplane";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractproviderconfigurationplane>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:providerconfigurationplane>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractproviderconfigurationplane> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractproviderconfigurationplane";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/providerconfigurationplane.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractproviderconfigurationplane>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractproviderconfigurationplane> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractproviderconfigurationplane";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/providerconfigurationplane.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerconfigurationplanesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractproviderconfigurationplane>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractproviderconfigurationplane>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractproviderconfigurationplane>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplanelifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplanelifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Manages provider configurations through an explicit lifecycle (proposed, configured, ready, degraded, disabled) so each provider instance is declared, validated, and promoted deliberately; it is provider-backed and database-backed but owns no tenant records. It deploys the V1-proven contract for GET/POST /api/admin/provider-configs plus the per-id lifecycle and delete operations and must keep its lifecycle/readiness model unchanged during extraction. Recovery re-runs proof:provider-config and proof:provider-readiness-contract before promotion continues.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerconfigurationplanesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplanestatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplanestatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State includes providerKey, capability, environment, instanceLabel, classification, lifecycleState (proposed, configured, ready, degraded, disabled), endpoint, config, credentialRef, requiresCredential, and audit metadata. Database changes use ordered SQL migrations that must preserve this proven state model, and rollback is forward-fix or guarded restore after migration lineage is verified. Credentials are referenced rather than embedded, keeping secret material out of the configuration record.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerconfigurationplanesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplanepermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplanepermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Provider-config operations are administrative endpoints; the plane owns no tenant data, so standard platform security controls govern access rather than per-tenant roles. Credential references are gated by requiresCredential and resolved through the secrets boundary rather than exposed in config reads. Mutating the lifecycle of a provider is an operator action that must keep mutation boundaries closed on failure.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerconfigurationplanesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplanecontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplanecontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The interface contract is the provider-config repository behind a port (provider-config-repository) plus the admin create/read, lifecycle-transition, and delete operations. Configuration is read from the declared provider/config plane and missing or invalid configuration fails closed rather than inventing defaults. The lifecycleState transitions are the contractual states consumers depend on to know whether a provider is usable.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerconfigurationplanesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplanevalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplanevalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Validation enforces required fields per provider, that credentialRef is present when requiresCredential is set, and that lifecycleState transitions are legal (for example, a provider cannot be ready without valid configuration). Inputs are validated before mutation and invalid configuration fails closed. Health is probed before a provider is allowed to reach the ready state.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerconfigurationplanesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplaneerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplaneerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Provider failure returns a typed degraded/readiness failure, keeps mutation boundaries closed, and does not fabricate successful provider state; degraded mode disables side-effect paths that depend on the HTTP health-probe adapter while keeping read-only readiness and audit visible. The risk class is semantic drift or configuration loss rather than tenant data loss. A failed health probe moves the provider to degraded rather than reporting false readiness.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerconfigurationplanesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplaneauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplaneauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State-changing provider-config operations follow audit-before-mutation behaviour with audit metadata on the record, capturing who changed a provider's configuration or lifecycle state. Audit and readiness signals remain visible in degraded mode. This preserves an honest, inspectable history of provider configuration changes.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerconfigurationplanesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplanereadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplanereadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is encoded directly in lifecycleState: a provider is ready only after it is configured, credentialed where required, and health-probed, and it degrades explicitly when the probe or substrate is unavailable. Readiness fails closed and stays visible read-only in degraded mode. Promotion is gated on proof:provider-config and proof:provider-readiness-contract passing.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerconfigurationplanesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplaneproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplaneproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by proof:provider-config and proof:provider-readiness-contract together with the cited auth-provider-config unit tests, demonstrating configuration, credential, lifecycle, and readiness semantics. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerconfigurationplanesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplaneuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerconfigurationplaneuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The providerconfigurationplane capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:providerconfigurationplane> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerenvironmentclassificationsemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
