<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractproviderenvironmentclassification> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractproviderenvironmentclassification";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/providerenvironmentclassification.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractproviderenvironmentclassification>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractproviderenvironmentclassification> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractproviderenvironmentclassification";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/providerenvironmentclassification.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerenvironmentclassificationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractproviderenvironmentclassification>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractproviderenvironmentclassification>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractproviderenvironmentclassification>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationlifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationlifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Classification capability that places each provider on an environment-posture axis (hermetic, local, sandbox, live) while keeping provider mode and environment as separate honest dimensions; it is provider-backed but owns no database schema. It deploys the V1-proven env-classification matrix contract and must keep its lifecycle/readiness model unchanged during extraction, with migrations limited to contract/config references that update semantic artefacts when behaviour changes. Recovery re-runs proof:provider-environment-classification before promotion continues.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerenvironmentclassificationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The state is the classification matrix: per provider/capability, its environment posture and the separation between provider mode and environment, held as configuration rather than owned tenant rows. It has no owned database schema, so backup scope is configuration/evidence only and restore cannot create tenant data. The matrix encodes that hermetic-mock must not be read as live-external and that environment must not upgrade provider mode by implication.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerenvironmentclassificationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "It owns no tenant records and exposes no tenant-mutating routes, so standard platform security controls apply; its tenant impact is indirect through correct posture labelling. Classification is an operator/governance concern, not an end-user permission. The separation it enforces is what prevents a hermetic or sandbox provider from being treated as production-live.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerenvironmentclassificationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract is the env-classification matrix that consumers read to know a provider's honest environment posture, mediated through configuration rather than a tenant API. Configuration is read from the declared provider/config plane and missing or invalid configuration fails closed instead of inventing defaults. The matrix is the authority other capabilities use to avoid overclaiming proof posture.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerenvironmentclassificationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Validation enforces the cross-dimension safety rules: provider mode and environment stay independent, hermetic-mock must not satisfy live-external-provider, and production-shaped must not satisfy production-live. Inputs are the per-provider posture declarations, which must be consistent and complete. Any classification that would upgrade posture by implication is rejected.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerenvironmentclassificationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Provider failure returns a typed degraded/readiness failure, keeps mutation boundaries closed, and does not fabricate successful provider state; degraded mode disables dependent side-effect paths while keeping read-only readiness and audit visible. The risk class is semantic drift or configuration loss, not tenant data loss. A blocked classification readiness or failing promotion proof is alertable.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerenvironmentclassificationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Because it owns no tenant mutation, its audit concern is the recorded classification lineage: changes to a provider's environment posture are captured as reviewable configuration/semantic changes. Readiness and audit stay visible in degraded mode. This preserves an honest, inspectable record that prevents posture inflation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerenvironmentclassificationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness means every relevant provider has an explicit, consistent environment classification with provider mode and environment kept separate; unavailable dependencies fail closed through the readiness model. Readiness is shown by re-running proof:provider-environment-classification rather than a live heartbeat. Stale or unknown classifications do not count as ready.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerenvironmentclassificationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Proof is proof:provider-environment-classification, demonstrating that the matrix keeps provider mode and environment as separate, honestly classified dimensions. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:providerenvironmentclassificationsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:providerenvironmentclassificationuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The providerenvironmentclassification capability is explicitly internal; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:providerenvironmentclassification> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:quotaenforcementsemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "quotaenforcementsemanticsource";
