    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:quotaenforcement>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "c90a7acd5cdc40bb9144ef7c6db4b2f27ff05a7c3871d06a3e2be56be19b4524";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/quota-enforcement.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:quotaenforcement> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractquotaenforcement>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractquotaenforcement> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractquotaenforcement";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractquotaenforcement>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:quotaenforcement>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractquotaenforcement> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractquotaenforcement";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/quotaenforcement.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractquotaenforcement>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractquotaenforcement> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractquotaenforcement";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/quotaenforcement.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:quotaenforcementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractquotaenforcement>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractquotaenforcement>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractquotaenforcement>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementlifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementlifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The quota lifecycle treats no configured quota as opt-in allowed, lets an operator set a quota with audit-before-upsert, evaluates entitlement before quota on each check, aggregates current usage, and returns a within/exceeded/no-entitlement/no-quota decision, throwing a typed denial for disallowed actions. Delta-aware checks include the requested increment (for example upload byte size) so a request that would cross the limit is denied before it is applied.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:quotaenforcementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State is a quota record (quota key, entitlement key, meter key, limit, window, deny action, updated-at/updated-by) plus a computed evaluation state of within, exceeded, no-entitlement, or no-quota, together with current usage, an allowed flag, and a projected usage value for delta checks. Usage is derived from the metering aggregate rather than stored independently.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:quotaenforcementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Tenant quota reads are tenant-scoped and operator set/update operations require operator authorization for a specified tenant; evaluation additionally requires the configured entitlement. Cross-tenant quota access is prevented and policy mutation is operator-only.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:quotaenforcementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The interface is a quota repository port exposing quota read, operator set/update, and an evaluation/assert operation that returns or enforces the allow/deny decision. The contract orders entitlement evaluation before quota comparison and supports projected-usage deltas for operations that add usage.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:quotaenforcementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Operator routes validate tenant identifiers and the set-quota request schema; the use case treats absent quota as opt-in allowed, validates entitlement before any usage comparison, and evaluates deltas for usage-adding operations. The entitlement-before-usage ordering is a load-bearing invariant.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:quotaenforcementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "An assert operation throws a typed denial once a quota is exceeded or the entitlement is revoked, while evaluation returns explicit denied decisions distinguishing no-entitlement from exceeded; no-quota resolves to allowed. Failures fail closed and do not grant usage on ambiguous provider state.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:quotaenforcementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Setting a quota emits an audit record before the mutation (audit-before-upsert) carrying the acting operator, and denial decisions are observable for enforcement. The quota resource is identified explicitly in audit metadata.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:quotaenforcementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is proven against live storage covering entitlement-before-quota ordering, the exceeded state, typed denial via assert, revoke-driven denial, and the no-quota allow path, with route handlers validated separately. When the quota substrate is unavailable, mutation paths are disabled and readiness degrades explicitly.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:quotaenforcementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by quota unit tests and runtime proofs validating live entitlement-before-quota ordering, exceeded state, typed denial, revoke denial, and route handlers. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:quotaenforcementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:quotaenforcementuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The quotaenforcement capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:quotaenforcement> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
