<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:runtimesecretsmanagementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractruntimesecretsmanagement>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractruntimesecretsmanagement>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractruntimesecretsmanagement>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementlifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementlifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The secret lifecycle is: put returns an opaque ref plus metadata, resolve returns the value only server-internally, rotate increments the version while keeping the same opaque ref, revoke disables resolution while retaining metadata, delete removes both metadata and the provider-held value, and readiness reports built-in and OpenBao backend health. A secret value is never returned by list or getMetadata; resolve is the single value-returning server path. Provider failure (OpenBao unreachable) reports degraded and never silently falls back to another backend.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:runtimesecretsmanagementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State comprises the secret ref, organisationId, name, provider in postgres|openbao, version, a revoked flag, the backend path, an encrypted_value for the built-in Postgres store or null when the value lives in OpenBao, and created, updated, and deleted metadata; list and getMetadata responses carry no value. The built-in store encrypts the value at rest while OpenBao holds the value entirely outside Postgres. Metadata is tenant-scoped under row-level security so refs do not leak across organisations.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:runtimesecretsmanagementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Admin secret routes require platform.secrets.read or platform.secrets.write and are operator-only; there is no tenant UI surface in this pass. Tenant isolation prevents one organisation from resolving, reading, or enumerating another organisation's ref, enforced at the store layer. This is a security-sensitive capability, so permission, audit, and fail-closed behaviour must be preserved on every path.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:runtimesecretsmanagementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract surface is GET and POST /api/admin/secrets, POST /api/admin/secrets/revoke, POST /api/admin/secrets/delete, and GET /api/admin/secrets/readiness, fronting a SecretStorePort with put, list, getMetadata, resolve, revoke, delete, and readiness operations behind the OpenBao and Postgres secret adapters. The port seam keeps the secret backend swappable, and resolve is deliberately the only value-returning operation. Readiness payloads carry no secret-bearing fields.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:runtimesecretsmanagementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Put returns no value, list and getMetadata are value-free, resolve is the only value-returning server path, rotation preserves the opaque ref while incrementing the version, OpenBao stores the value outside Postgres, and readiness payloads contain no secret-bearing fields. These invariants are exercised by the secret-store contract and OpenBao proofs to guarantee values never leak through metadata or readiness surfaces.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:runtimesecretsmanagementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Outcomes are deterministic and fail closed: a revoked, deleted, or cross-tenant ref resolves to null; an unreachable OpenBao reports degraded; an unavailable built-in Postgres degrades or skips honestly in proof; and no contract echoes a secret value on any failure path. Degraded mode disables the adapter-dependent mutation paths while keeping read-only readiness and audit visible, and no silent fallback upgrades provider readiness.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:runtimesecretsmanagementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "put, revoke, and delete emit audit-before-change records carrying only name, ref, and provider metadata and never the value, so the audit write precedes the store mutation. Where the use-case wraps the store write, an audit failure prevents the mutation, making audit a hard precondition for change. This guarantees a complete, value-free audit trail for every secret-lifecycle action.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:runtimesecretsmanagementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness distinguishes built-in Postgres ready, OpenBao ready, and OpenBao degraded or unreachable, and emits secret-free readiness payloads; the built-in check is a Postgres SELECT 1 and the OpenBao check is its sys/health endpoint, and an OpenBao outage yields degraded rather than a fabricated ready. No silent fallback upgrades provider readiness, so a hermetic or composed state is never reported as a live-external-provider state.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:runtimesecretsmanagementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by three runtime proofs: secret-store-contract validates the live Postgres store contract, encryption, row-level security, and audit; secrets-openbao validates the live OpenBao provider; and provider-secrets-readiness validates the ready versus degraded classification, described in the corpus as level-4 live provider and storage validation. The proofs are the lineage evidence, not a USF readiness claim. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:runtimesecretsmanagementsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:runtimesecretsmanagementuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The runtimesecretsmanagement capability is explicitly internal; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:runtimesecretsmanagement> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratesemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratesemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:s1942bb091c25935d3b697345ee1c8cbfd5332d0a24d74264916a1cbddcadb770>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "4dffb8a483146dc8c9009eefbc96176f09d5e55acc73cda02e600086442d12dd";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/scheduled-jobs-built-in-on-the-event-substrate.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractscheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractscheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractscheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractscheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractscheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractscheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractscheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractscheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractscheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractscheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractscheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractscheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratelifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratelifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "An operator creates a schedule, the enabled job persists, a due tick enqueues a platform event, a same-window tick deduplicates so no duplicate event is enqueued, pausing disables due enqueue, run-now enqueues an event immediately, and an operator patch toggles the enabled flag. Scheduled dispatch is built directly on the event substrate, so an enqueued job becomes an ordinary platform_events record (for example a report.run event) carried by the durable-queue retry and dead-letter machinery. The daemon tick is invocable even though the continuous daemon loop is not claimed wired.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratestatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratestatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State is the scheduled_jobs table holding organisationId, jobKey, eventType, intervalSeconds, an enabled flag, nextRunAt, and lastRunAt, together with an event idempotency window that prevents duplicate enqueue within the same due window. Enqueued jobs materialise as platform_events on the shared event substrate, so downstream state, ordering, retry, and dead-letter follow the event-bus state model. Row-level security scopes scheduled jobs to the owning organisation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratepermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratepermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Scheduled-job routes are global, operator-only platform surfaces: listing requires platform.jobs.read while create, run-now, and patch require platform.jobs.write. The due tick is server-internal and is not callable from tenant UI. Tenant isolation is enforced by organisationId scoping and row-level security so one organisation cannot list or trigger another organisation's jobs.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratecontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratecontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract surface is GET and POST /api/admin/scheduled-jobs, POST /api/admin/scheduled-jobs/:jobId/run, and PATCH /api/admin/scheduled-jobs/:jobId, with the periodic due tick exposed only as a server-internal operation behind the EventBusPort and PostgresEventBusAdapter. Enqueue is expressed as event publication, so the scheduled-job contract composes with the event-bus contract rather than duplicating delivery semantics. The port seam keeps the substrate provider swappable.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratevalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratevalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "List routes require organisationId, invalid job ids are rejected, create validates the schedule body, run-now validates the job id, and the same-window idempotency window prevents duplicate event enqueue for a job that has already fired in the current window. Disabled jobs are never enqueued by the due tick. These invariants are exercised by the scheduled-jobs and scheduled-job-routes runtime proofs.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrateerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrateerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Outcomes are deterministic and fail closed: a missing organisationId returns 400, an invalid job id returns 400, a disabled job is simply not due, a repeated due tick within the window is deduplicated, and an unavailable Postgres substrate yields an honest skip or readiness failure rather than a fabricated enqueue. Errors are typed and tenant-scoped and never silently drop scheduled work.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrateauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrateauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "scheduled_job.set and scheduled_job.run are audit-before-change operations, so the audit record is written before the schedule mutation or manual run takes effect. The recurring due-tick enqueue is represented operationally by the resulting platform_events records rather than as a separate user-mutation audit event. This keeps operator intent auditable while treating routine dispatch as operational telemetry.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratereadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratereadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is that the due tick is invocable and the routes are accessible, even though the continuous daemon loop is not claimed; the live proof validates the table schema, row-level-security isolation, due/run-now enqueue behaviour, and the route handlers, and degrades explicitly when the substrate is unavailable. Because dispatch rides the event substrate, scheduled-job readiness inherits the event-bus degraded posture and never reports production-shaped behaviour as production-live.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrateproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrateproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by two runtime proofs: scheduled-jobs validates live Postgres schedule persistence, due and run-now enqueue, row-level security, and the no-secret schema, and scheduled-job-routes validates the route handlers and access metadata, described in the corpus as level-4 live substrate and route validation. The proofs are the lineage evidence, not a USF readiness claim. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstratesemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrateuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrateuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:scheduledjobsbuiltinontheeventsubstrate> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:searchandindexingproductsearchsemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "searchandindexingproductsearchsemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:s384c372c2f1fb4474938dbc56c7755577795eafdaaac9a525d262bc06bd6432b>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:searchandindexingproductsearch>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "fcc4e6af05975516ae183478fe05cb11e577797e0546db712412fc3846610e6e";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/search-and-indexing-product-search.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:searchandindexingproductsearch> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractsearchandindexingproductsearch>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractsearchandindexingproductsearch> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractsearchandindexingproductsearch";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractsearchandindexingproductsearch>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:searchandindexingproductsearch>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractsearchandindexingproductsearch> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractsearchandindexingproductsearch";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/searchandindexingproductsearch.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractsearchandindexingproductsearch>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractsearchandindexingproductsearch> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractsearchandindexingproductsearch";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/searchandindexingproductsearch.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:searchandindexingproductsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractsearchandindexingproductsearch>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractsearchandindexingproductsearch>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractsearchandindexingproductsearch>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchlifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchlifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Provides tenant product search backed by full-text indexing with a reindex path and a readiness probe, exposed through tenant search and admin search readiness and reindex operations; documents are indexed into a tenant-scoped relational full-text store and queried with permission gating. Indexed documents are kept in sync with their sources and can be rebuilt via reindex. The search engine is a full-text-search adapter behind a port, with alternative engines available as future provider adapters.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:searchandindexingproductsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Each indexed document carries a tenant/organisation id, document id, document type, title, a full-text search vector with an associated index, a URL, non-secret metadata, and an optional permission key, with uniqueness on tenant plus type plus document id. Readiness is reported as a full-text-search engine with status ready, degraded, or blocked. The index store is a tenant-scoped relational table under row-level security and excludes secret fields from indexed metadata.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:searchandindexingproductsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Search results are isolated by tenant under the canonical row-level-security predicate and further gated by an optional per-document permission key so a user only sees documents they are entitled to, never another tenant's documents. Admin readiness and reindex are operator-scoped privileged operations. Indexed metadata deliberately omits secret fields so the search surface cannot leak sensitive values.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:searchandindexingproductsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract exposes a tenant search query plus admin search readiness and reindex, all mediated through the search repository/query port and full-text adapter. The query contract enforces tenant isolation and permission-key gating, and the index contract maintains the document shape (search vector, metadata without secrets, optional permission key) with its uniqueness constraint. Reindex rebuilds the tenant-scoped index from sources.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:searchandindexingproductsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Queries are validated and scoped to the tenant and, where present, the permission key, so unscoped or cross-tenant queries are rejected; indexing validates the document shape and uniqueness on tenant/type/document id. Readiness is validated by a probe reporting ready, degraded, or blocked. Missing or invalid configuration fails closed rather than returning unscoped results.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:searchandindexingproductsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearcherrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearcherrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The model is fail-closed: a query under one tenant context must return zero rows from another tenant, an unready engine reports degraded or blocked rather than serving stale or unscoped results, and provider failure returns a typed degraded or readiness error with mutation boundaries closed. The search surface never fabricates results or exposes secret metadata. Tenant data cannot be silently dropped or remapped.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:searchandindexingproductsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Search and reindex operations preserve tenant context through route/use-case/provider spans, with typed error logs carrying the tenant/organisation identifier when tenant-scoped, and readiness transitions are observable as a signal. Indexed metadata excludes secrets so audit and logs do not surface sensitive content. Recovery must preserve tenant boundary and audit.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:searchandindexingproductsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is reported by the full-text engine probe as ready, degraded, or blocked, and is verified by isolation and route proofs; the capability degrades explicitly when the search adapter is unavailable, disabling index mutation while keeping read-only readiness and audit visible. Readiness being blocked, a failed search/search-isolation/search-routes proof during promotion, or a missing isolation or audit signal raise alerts and block promotion.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:searchandindexingproductsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by the search, search-isolation, and search-routes proofs, including a cross-tenant isolation assertion that a foreign-tenant query returns zero rows. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:searchandindexingproductsearchsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:searchandindexingproductsearchuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The searchandindexingproductsearch capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:searchandindexingproductsearch> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
