<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractservicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodel> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractservicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodel";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodel.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractservicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodel>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractservicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodel> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractservicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodel";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodel.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractservicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodel>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractservicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodel>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractservicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodel>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodellifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodellifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Registers platform services and their provider integration model, governing how each service is built, composed, or adapted and how it is exposed; it is provider-backed, database-backed, and touches tenant data. It deploys the V1-proven contract for platform-services readiness and GET /api/platform/service-catalog (catalog v2) and must keep its lifecycle/readiness model unchanged during extraction. Recovery re-runs proof:platform-services, proof:service-clickthrough-policy, proof:service-catalog-registry, and proof:entitlements-routes before promotion continues.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State includes each service's key, name, and category; its environment model; visibility (tenant_scoped_safe, global_only, or not_exposed); the integration decision (build, compose, adapter, defer, or reject); the entitlement key; proof references; console-access flags; readiness status; and provider details. Database changes use ordered SQL migrations that must preserve this proven state model, and rollback is forward-fix or guarded restore after migration lineage is verified so tenant data is never silently dropped or remapped. As a tenant-data participant it is subject to tenant backup/export/retention/legal-hold semantics.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Because it can affect tenant-visible data or access, it must preserve tenant isolation: visibility classifications (tenant_scoped_safe vs global_only vs not_exposed) and entitlement keys gate what each tenant can see and reach. Mutating operations are administrative and must keep mutation boundaries closed on failure. Tenant-scoped reads and clickthrough access are governed by the recorded visibility and entitlement model.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The interface contract is the platform-services readiness surface and the service-catalog read API behind ports/adapters, returning catalog entries with their decision, visibility, entitlement, and readiness fields. Configuration is read from the declared provider/config plane and missing or invalid configuration fails closed rather than inventing UI defaults. Provider integration is mediated through ports so adapters can be swapped without changing the catalog contract.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Validation enforces that each catalog entry has a coherent decision, visibility, entitlement, and readiness state, that tenant-scoped exposure is safe, and that provider details resolve. Inputs are checked before mutation and missing or invalid configuration fails closed. It guards against exposing a service more broadly than its visibility classification permits.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Provider failure returns a typed degraded/readiness failure, keeps mutation boundaries closed, and does not fabricate successful provider state; degraded mode disables side-effecting paths that depend on the observability adapters while keeping read-only readiness and audit visible. Tenant data loss is possible only if migration, restore, or export semantics are bypassed, which the error model forbids. A missing tenant isolation or audit signal is an alertable tenant-data-or-security condition.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State-changing catalog and integration actions follow audit-before-mutation behaviour recovered from the source lineage and tests, recording the actor and change so the tenant boundary and DSR/GDPR evidence are preserved. Audit and readiness signals stay visible in degraded mode. Recovery preserves tenant boundary and audit evidence rather than silently overwriting it.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness reflects whether each service's providers resolve and its catalog entry is coherent; it degrades explicitly when the underlying substrate (for example the observability adapters) is unavailable rather than reporting false health. Readiness fails closed and remains visible read-only in degraded mode. Promotion is gated on the named platform-services and catalog proofs passing.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by proof:platform-services, proof:service-clickthrough-policy, proof:service-catalog-registry, and proof:entitlements-routes together with the cited unit tests, demonstrating catalog, visibility, entitlement, and readiness semantics. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodelsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodeluisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodeluisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodel capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:servicecatalogandproviderintegrationmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
