    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:suborganisations>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractsuborganisations> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractsuborganisations";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/suborganisations.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractsuborganisations>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractsuborganisations> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractsuborganisations";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/suborganisations.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:suborganisationssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractsuborganisations>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractsuborganisations>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractsuborganisations>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationslifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationslifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Sub-organisation lifecycle is list active child organisations, create with a slug and display name, update the display name, and deactivate by clearing the active flag. Deactivation is a soft state change rather than a hard delete.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:suborganisationssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationsstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationsstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State is an organisation row carrying parent id, slug, display name, active flag, and timestamps, exposed to the API as a flat tenant-scoped list while the parent id is kept internal. Children are always anchored to a resolved parent tenant.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:suborganisationssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationspermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationspermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Routes require the specific sub-organisation read, create, update, or delete permission, are tenant-scoped, and declare a sub-organisation resource and matching scopes. Tenant isolation is enforced by filtering on the resolved parent id.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:suborganisationssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationscontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationscontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The operation surface lists and creates sub-organisations and updates or deactivates a sub-organisation by id. Mutations return typed results mapped to standard responses.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:suborganisationssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationsvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationsvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Creation validates a lowercase slug's length, characters, and no edge hyphen, validates display-name length, rejects reserved slugs, and rejects a duplicate global slug, while update requires at least a display name with a length check. Invalid input is rejected before any change.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:suborganisationssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationserrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationserrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Typed outcomes include invalid-body, reserved-slug, conflict, not-found, and ok, mapped fail-closed to 400/422/409/404/201/200/204; provider failure returns a typed degraded result and keeps mutation boundaries closed. No partial child state is persisted on failure.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:suborganisationssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationsauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationsauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Create, update, and deactivate emit sub-organisation created, updated, and deactivated audit-before-change events, and audit failure aborts the insert, update, or deactivation. Read-only listing is not audited.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:suborganisationssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationsreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationsreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is invariant-ready once the organisations table is available; because that table has no row-level security, every query explicitly filters by the parent id from the resolved tenant context, and degraded mode disables store-dependent mutation while keeping read-only listing visible.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:suborganisationssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationsproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationsproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "A unit proof covers the state machine and validation and a UI semantic harness proves the headless journey, demonstrated in source lineage via hermetic state/validation proof plus a semantic harness for future UI generation. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:suborganisationssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationsuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:suborganisationsuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The suborganisations capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:suborganisations> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
