<urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunset> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantcanonicaldomainsetunset>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantcanonicaldomainsetunset> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracttenantcanonicaldomainsetunset";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantcanonicaldomainsetunset>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunset>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantcanonicaldomainsetunset> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracttenantcanonicaldomainsetunset";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/tenantcanonicaldomainsetunset.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracttenantcanonicaldomainsetunset>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracttenantcanonicaldomainsetunset> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracttenantcanonicaldomainsetunset";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/tenantcanonicaldomainsetunset.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantcanonicaldomainsetunset>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantcanonicaldomainsetunset>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantcanonicaldomainsetunset>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetlifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetlifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Canonical designation is a guarded set/unset: setting is refused when the domain is not verified, the auth client is inactive, or local routing is not proven, and a successful set flips the canonical flag and the redirect policy to redirect-slug-to-canonical. A second set atomically replaces the prior canonical domain, unset clears the flag, and deactivating the domain also clears canonical.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State is a canonical boolean plus a canonical timestamp and the redirect policy, constrained so at most one enabled canonical domain exists per tenant. Canonical is a marker only: it does not upgrade routing status or TLS status, which remain governed by their own lifecycle.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Canonical set and unset require the tenant-scoped domain-write permission and operate only on the owning tenant's domains. The single-canonical-per-tenant invariant is enforced within that tenant's scope.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract surface is a canonical set operation and a canonical unset operation backed by set/unset canonical use cases, mediated by the tenant-domain port and auth-client adapter. The semantics are expressed abstractly against the port rather than a concrete provider.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Setting canonical requires verified ownership, an active auth client, and proven local routing, while unset requires the domain to exist, and a second set preserves the one-canonical invariant by atomically replacing the existing canonical row. These preconditions are checked before any state mutation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunseterrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunseterrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Outcomes are typed and fail-closed as ok, not-found, not-verified, auth-client-inactive, or routing-not-proven, so each unmet precondition produces a distinct deterministic result rather than a partial change. The replacement of an existing canonical is atomic so the invariant cannot be transiently violated.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Set and unset emit canonical set and unset audit events carrying domain and redirect-policy metadata before the registry mutation. Audit precedes the state change so every canonical transition is recorded ahead of being applied.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness covers local canonical cutover only; public DNS and TLS are explicitly deferred, and canonical is treated as a marker that does not imply public routing or TLS readiness. The capability therefore degrades honestly to a local-only posture when external infrastructure is unavailable.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by a canonical-domain runtime proof that validates live registry guards, redirect-policy transition, atomic replacement, unset, and clearing on deactivation against a real substrate. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunsetuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The tenantcanonicaldomainsetunset capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantcanonicaldomainsetunset> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantdataimportexportsemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
