<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantdomainactivationauthclientsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantdomainactivationauthclient>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantdomainactivationauthclient>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantdomainactivationauthclient>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientlifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientlifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Auth-client activation transitions a domain from inactive to active only after ownership is verified, the activation audit is emitted, and the auth-client port successfully adds the redirect origin; deactivation transitions active back to inactive, removes the origin, and clears canonical and routing state. The external auth-client mutation is the final, gating step so the registry only reflects activation that actually took effect.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantdomainactivationauthclientsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State is the domain's auth-client status (inactive or active) together with an activation timestamp, the canonical flag, routing status, and a disabled guard. If the auth-client port throws during activation the active marker is never written, so registry state cannot drift ahead of the external configuration.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantdomainactivationauthclientsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Activation and deactivation require the tenant-scoped domain-write permission, and the domain-only operation no longer requires the broader auth-settings write permission. Operations are tenant-isolated to the owning tenant's domains.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantdomainactivationauthclientsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract surface is an activate operation and a corresponding deactivate operation backed by activate/deactivate auth-client use cases, mediated by the tenant-domain port and an auth-client adapter. The semantics are expressed against the port so activation is independent of the specific identity-provider implementation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantdomainactivationauthclientsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Activation refuses not-found, not-verified, and already-active before any audit or external mutation, and deactivation refuses not-found and not-active. These guards run ahead of side effects so an invalid request never reaches the auth-client port.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantdomainactivationauthclientsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclienterrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclienterrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Outcomes are typed and fail-closed as ok, not-found, not-verified, already-active, or not-active; a thrown auth-client port error leaves the registry inactive because the active marker is only written after the port call succeeds. Error handling therefore preserves the invariant that registry state matches external state.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantdomainactivationauthclientsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Activation and deactivation emit auth-client activated and deactivated audit events with safe, domain-only metadata before the auth-client port mutation. Audit precedes the external change, so the attempt is always recorded even if the provider call later fails.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantdomainactivationauthclientsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The capability is invariant-ready once ownership is verified and the auth-client mutation has succeeded, but activation explicitly does not imply routing or TLS readiness. Readiness is therefore scoped to the auth-client dimension and degrades to inactive when the external mutation cannot complete.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantdomainactivationauthclientsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by unit proofs over the domain lifecycle guards and by a canonical-domain runtime proof that validates live registry behaviour with an injected auth-client port. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantdomainactivationauthclientsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantdomainactivationauthclientuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The tenantdomainactivationauthclient capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantdomainactivationauthclient> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantgroupssemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "tenantgroupssemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:s254d30906c8facb151be516cb10f189f248a0133b2c65daed343ab04a4135ae5>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantgroups>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "91738fe4c95d7483ea38c993588202e11d6376569157e3feede410c49531e752";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/tenant-groups.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantgroups> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantgroups>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantgroups> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracttenantgroups";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantgroups>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantgroups>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantgroups> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracttenantgroups";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/tenantgroups.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracttenantgroups>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracttenantgroups> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracttenantgroups";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/tenantgroups.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantgroupssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantgroups>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantgroups>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantgroups>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupslifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupslifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Group lifecycle is list existing groups, create after name validation and a duplicate check, update after existence and conflict checks, and delete after a protected-name guard. Each mutation runs its precondition checks before touching the provider.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantgroupssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupsstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupsstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State is a tenant-realm group identified by id, name, and path, with reserved names protected; groups live in the identity provider's realm and are not persisted in the relational store. The group set is scoped to the tenant realm.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantgroupssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupspermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupspermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Routes require the specific group read, create, update, or delete permission, are tenant-scoped, and declare a group resource and matching scopes, resolving the tenant realm credential from context. One tenant cannot manage another tenant's groups.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantgroupssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupscontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupscontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The operation surface lists and creates groups and updates or deletes a group by id, backed by the tenant-credential realm admin adapter. Mutations return typed results mapped to standard responses.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantgroupssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupsvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupsvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Group names must be non-empty strings of at most 64 characters with no path separators or control characters, must not be reserved, and must not duplicate an existing name case-insensitively. Invalid names are rejected before any provider write.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantgroupssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupserrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupserrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Typed outcomes include invalid-name, conflict, not-found, protected, and ok, mapped fail-closed to 400/409/404/422/201/204, and a missing tenant credential returns a no-credential/503 result; provider failure keeps mutation boundaries closed. No partial group state is left behind.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantgroupssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupsauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupsauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Create, update, and delete emit group-created, group-updated, and group-deleted audit-before-change events after precondition checks, and audit failure aborts the provider mutation. Read-only listing is not audited.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantgroupssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupsreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupsreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Semantic readiness is invariant-ready, while route execution additionally requires tenant context and the tenant-realm auth-settings credential, and degraded mode disables provider-dependent mutation while keeping read-only readiness visible. A UI semantic harness proves the generation contract without shipping a legacy page.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantgroupssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupsproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupsproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "A unit proof covers group lifecycle and validation and a UI semantic harness proves the headless journey, demonstrated in source lineage via hermetic behaviour/state validation plus a semantic harness for future UI generation. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantgroupssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupsuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantgroupsuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The tenantgroups capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantgroups> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenanthostidentityresolutionsemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "tenanthostidentityresolutionsemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:s99fda846177298be25c2c89dcc52256262de4eec0c48795785b623b860dd6d71>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenanthostidentityresolution>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "131ab3dfe55ad6c8a1963f34f020848049d926e1fe64faa318cc218f429c550e";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/tenant-host-identity-resolution.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenanthostidentityresolution> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenanthostidentityresolution>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenanthostidentityresolution> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracttenanthostidentityresolution";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
