<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantidentityrecordandfqdn>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantidentityrecordandfqdn>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantidentityrecordandfqdn>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnlifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnlifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Tenant identity covers provisioning of a tenant record and resolution of request hosts to that tenant: apex, reserved, invalid, and malformed hosts resolve to no tenant, seeded slug FQDNs resolve with a slug host source, and active verified custom domains resolve through the domain registry with a custom-domain host source. Provisioning is operator-driven and host resolution is a deterministic per-request derivation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State includes the organisation id, slug/FQDN, a derived realm name of the form tenant-{organisationId}, a host source (slug, custom_domain, or fixture), and the per-FQDN domain-registry states for custom domains. A custom domain only contributes tenant context once it is verified and active.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Tenant provisioning is operator-controlled and gated by platform tenant read/create permissions, while host-identity resolution is read-only request context that grants no data access without the route's own permission checks. Tenant isolation is preserved because resolution never produces a partial or fallback tenant.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdncontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdncontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The operation surface provides tenant provisioning and a host-identity lookup, with runtime resolution consuming the request Host / forwarded-host headers. The contract returns the resolved tenant context or an explicit no-tenant result.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Host validation classifies apex, slug, local slug, reserved, unknown, malformed, host-with-port, and possible-custom-domain cases, and forwarded-host precedence is enforced deterministically. Custom domains must be verified and active to be accepted.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Invalid, unknown, reserved, apex, and inactive/pending/disabled custom hosts resolve fail-closed to a null tenant context rather than to a partial or fallback tenant, and provider failure returns a typed degraded result without fabricating tenant state. No untrusted host is ever silently served as a tenant.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Tenant provisioning is audited at the provisioning surface, while host-identity resolution is read-only and carries no mutation audit, with failed resolution logged rather than audited. Audit precedes the provisioning change.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is invariant-ready once the resolver and domain registry are available, and degraded mode disables registry-dependent mutation while keeping read-only resolution and audit visible. Live proofs skip honestly when seeded local substrate is absent rather than faking tenant resolution.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "A runtime domain-identity matrix proof validates host classification plus live slug resolution, and a custom-domain resolution proof validates live registry resolution with rejection of inactive, pending, and disabled domains and a unique-enabled-domain guard. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantidentityrecordandfqdnuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The tenantidentityrecordandfqdn capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantidentityrecordandfqdn> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantisolationproofsemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "tenantisolationproofsemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:safe7ba9f71db4b18e17f4e5db3ec6fc5164f23911f3149003333648f9dde5cdf>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantisolationproof>;
