    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantisolationproof>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantisolationproof> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracttenantisolationproof";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/tenantisolationproof.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracttenantisolationproof>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracttenantisolationproof> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracttenantisolationproof";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/tenantisolationproof.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantisolationproofsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantisolationproof>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantisolationproof>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantisolationproof>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationprooflifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationprooflifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The isolation lifecycle resolves host identity, binds the request context to exactly one organisation, enforces tenant-scoped repositories, row-level security, and storage prefixes, rejects cross-tenant reads and writes, and verifies isolation through domain, storage, search, metering, observability, webhook, and secret proofs. Untrusted hosts never acquire a tenant context.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantisolationproofsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State includes host classifications (apex, slug, reserved, unknown, malformed, custom domain), the resolved tenant context (organisation identifier, slug, host source), the row-level-security tenant setting in the database, the object-storage tenant prefix, and a null tenant context for untrusted hosts. Host source distinguishes slug-resolved from active verified custom-domain resolution.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantisolationproofsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Permissions are enforced only after tenant resolution; unresolved, apex, or reserved hosts grant no tenant context, tenant actors access only their own organisation's rows and prefixes, and operator bypass requires an explicit bypass/system role. Host identity is read-only and does not by itself grant data access.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantisolationproofsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract surface is host-identity resolution, tenant-aware route context, storage prefixes, row-level-security-backed repository ports, and readiness proofs for tenant-scoped substrates. Resolution consumes the forwarded host header with defined precedence and binds a single organisation per request.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantisolationproofsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Validation proves slug and custom-domain resolution, forwarded-host precedence, null outcomes for apex/reserved/unknown/malformed hosts, storage prefix isolation, foreign-key rejection, and cross-tenant row-level-security counts of zero. Inactive, pending, or disabled custom domains are rejected rather than resolved.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantisolationproofsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationprooferrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationprooferrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Untrusted hosts resolve to a null tenant context, absent or unverified custom domains are rejected, foreign tenant data is hidden or rejected, and provider failures degrade readiness rather than falling back to an unsafe tenant. The system fails closed to no-tenant rather than guessing a tenant.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantisolationproofsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Isolation checks are guard behaviour and do not emit mutation audit directly; audited mutations in tenant-scoped capabilities carry tenant/organisation metadata and fail before any cross-tenant write. The guard prevents the unsafe write before audit-bearing operations run.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantisolationproofsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Isolation readiness is proven by live substrate checks for the resolver, row-level security, storage prefixes, and tenant-scoped provider probes, with an unavailable provider treated as degraded/unreachable rather than isolated. Readiness reflects proven isolation, not assumed isolation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantisolationproofsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by domain-identity-matrix and tenant-storage isolation runtime proofs plus live row-level-security isolation checks across metering, search, observability, webhooks, events, and secret-store proofs. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantisolationproofsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantisolationproofuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The tenantisolationproof capability is explicitly internal; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantisolationproof> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
