    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracttenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexport>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracttenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexport> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracttenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexport";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexport.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexport>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexport>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexport>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportlifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportlifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Lifecycle operations are explicit and ordered: provision creates the tenant, suspend coordinates data, storage, realm, then DSR after audit, and delete exports first and then coordinates storage, realm, DSR, and data. A coordinator sequences these subsystem transitions so destructive steps occur in a defined order.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Tenant lifecycle state is represented by coordinated subsystem outcomes and export metadata: suspend returns coordinated [data, storage, realm, DSR]; delete returns coordinated [export, storage, realm, DSR, data] plus an export digest and key reference. The export is produced before deletion so a portable archive exists prior to destructive steps.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The capability is operator-controlled through platform tenant permissions with a system-admin actor context, and every lifecycle operation scopes by organisation identifier. Route handlers validate tenant identifiers before any lifecycle action.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportcontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportcontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract is a tenant-lifecycle coordinator exposing export, suspend-data/storage/realm/DSR, and delete-data/storage/realm/DSR operations plus the admin tenant route family for provision, suspend, delete, export, and import. The coordinator is the interface that orders subsystem calls.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Delete refuses to continue after a subsystem coordination failure, so a failed realm deletion stops before DSR and data deletion. Tenant identifiers are validated at the route boundary and export must succeed before delete proceeds.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexporterrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexporterrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Subsystem failures propagate as typed or ordinary errors and halt later destructive steps; for example a realm-deletion failure leaves the recorded calls at export, delete-storage, delete-realm with no further deletion. Failures fail closed so partial destruction does not silently complete.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Suspend and delete emit audit before subsystem coordination, and both unit and runtime proof assert that the audit is invoked first. Lifecycle transitions are audited so provisioning, suspension, deletion, and export are attributable.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Runtime readiness is the tenant-lifecycle proof, which validates audit-first behaviour and the subsystem coordination order for suspend and delete. Readiness degrades explicitly when the lifecycle coordinator substrate is unavailable.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by tenant-lifecycle unit tests and a runtime proof asserting audit-first invocation and ordered subsystem coordination with export-before-delete. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexportuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexport capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantlifecycleprovisionsuspenddeleteexport> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
