    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracttenantserviceclickthroughpolicy";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantserviceclickthroughpolicy>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicy>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantserviceclickthroughpolicy> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracttenantserviceclickthroughpolicy";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/tenantserviceclickthroughpolicy.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracttenantserviceclickthroughpolicy>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontracttenantserviceclickthroughpolicy> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontracttenantserviceclickthroughpolicy";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/tenantserviceclickthroughpolicy.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantserviceclickthroughpolicy>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontracttenantserviceclickthroughpolicy>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontracttenantserviceclickthroughpolicy>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicylifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicylifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Decides, per tenant and per service, whether a user may click through to an internal/composed service and derives the forward-auth allow sets plus the reverse-proxy (Caddyfile) reconciliation that enforce that decision at the edge. The capability is provider- and database-backed and owns tenant-affecting access policy, so its lifecycle/readiness model must be preserved and reconciliation kept consistent with the policy.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicystatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicystatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Persisted state includes per-service descriptors (id, resource, apex path, tenant path, classification), a landing path, a dev-only flag, and the system-admin and tenant-admin resource sets, from which an access decision (granted plus reason) and a clickthrough URL are derived. State evolves through ordered, forward-only migrations that preserve the proven policy/decision model and cannot silently drop or remap tenant access rules.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicypermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicypermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Clickthrough decisions are the permission model: access is computed from system-admin and tenant-admin resource sets and the service classification, and the resulting forward-auth sets gate edge access per tenant. This is a security-sensitive surface where permission, audit, and fail-closed behaviour must be preserved; a service not explicitly granted is denied, and dev-only services are excluded outside the appropriate context.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicycontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicycontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Exposes an access-decision operation that returns granted/denied with a reason and a clickthrough URL, behind ports/adapters so the reverse-proxy reconciler is swappable without changing the policy contract. The derived forward-auth sets and reconciled proxy configuration are the contract's side effects, kept deterministic so the edge enforcement always matches the computed policy.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicyvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicyvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Service descriptors, classification, and resource-set membership are validated before a decision is derived, and missing or invalid configuration fails closed rather than granting access by default. The dev-only flag and tenant/path bindings are checked so a malformed or out-of-context request cannot produce an over-broad clickthrough URL.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicyerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicyerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Provider or reconciler failure returns a typed degraded/readiness failure and keeps mutation boundaries closed, never fabricating a granted decision or a successful reconciliation. Because access is tenant-affecting, a denied or indeterminate decision defaults to no access, and tenant data/policy loss is possible only if migration/restore semantics are bypassed.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicyauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicyauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Access decisions and policy/reconciliation changes are recorded as auditable events before edge configuration is applied, preserving tenant boundary, the decision reason, and DSR/GDPR evidence. A missing tenant-isolation or audit signal on a clickthrough decision is an explicit alert condition.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicyreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicyreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness reflects whether policy derivation and proxy reconciliation are healthy and degrades explicitly when the reconciler or substrate is unavailable, disabling reconciliation side-effects while keeping read-only readiness and audit visible. Emitted readiness, error, and audit signals use the controlled, OpenTelemetry-informed observability vocabulary.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicyproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicyproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by the cited service-clickthrough-policy and clickthrough runtime proofs plus service-clickthrough tests, demonstrating per-tenant access decisions and forward-auth/reconciliation derivation as hermetic/runtime lineage rather than a current-readiness claim. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicysemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicyuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicyuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The tenantserviceclickthroughpolicy capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:tenantserviceclickthroughpolicy> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplessemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplessemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:sa99d7cbd561d28b9bae0a23276d26a715640257983e1d56cad6d434bae6a1c7a>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "5094ed17eb904556dc914272604e91ce77e1c86a0b59b4d28ef6b0ced82fc58c";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/universal-service-foundation-scope-and-principles.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractuniversalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractuniversalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractuniversalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractuniversalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractuniversalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractuniversalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractuniversalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractuniversalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractuniversalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractuniversalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractuniversalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractuniversalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprincipleslifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprincipleslifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Governing meta-capability that defines the foundation's posture (semantic-first, evidence-backed, hermetically provable, AI-safe) and the lifecycle every other capability must honour rather than a CRUD service of its own. Its operational lifecycle is the V2 extraction lifecycle: each capability deploys a V1-proven contract and must keep its semanticCompleteness lifecycle/readiness model unchanged through extraction, with promotion only after the foundation matrix, registry, and validation checks pass. It owns no tenant records and is classified as a provider-dependency foundation concern whose health is the integrity of the foundation asset graph.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplesstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplesstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The state is the foundation asset graph itself: the capability inventory, the status vocabulary, V2 targets, completion actions, the path map, the proof inventory, the migration chain, package status, the service matrix, and validator findings. It holds no tenant data; its state is configuration- and evidence-shaped, so backup scope is configuration/evidence only and restore can never fabricate tenant records. State changes are governed by deliberate semantic decisions rather than runtime mutations.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplespermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplespermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "As a shared platform-governance asset it owns no tenant-scoped records and exposes no tenant-mutating routes, so standard platform security controls apply rather than per-tenant authorization. Authority over changes flows through the USF constitutional and authority order (semantic definitions, ADRs, validators, proof, then source), not through end-user roles. Its effect on tenants is indirect: it constrains shared platform behaviour without owning or exposing tenant data.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplescontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplescontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract is normative rather than an HTTP surface (the V1 contract reference is n/a): it asserts the principles, authority order, and provability guarantees that bind every capability's interface and extraction. Configuration is read from the declared provider/config plane and missing or invalid configuration fails closed instead of inventing defaults. Conformant capabilities must preserve their proven lifecycle/readiness contract during extraction and keep mutation boundaries closed under failure.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplesvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplesvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Validation enforces that the foundation's invariants hold across the corpus: proof level is not report status, readiness claims must not exceed observed evidence, hermetic proof must not be upgraded to live external proof, and production-shaped must not be treated as production-live. It validates the asset graph for semantic drift and configuration loss, and treats stale or unknown signals as not-pass. Inputs that would violate the authority order or naming rules are rejected at the governance boundary.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprincipleserrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprincipleserrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Failures fail closed: provider or dependency failure returns a typed degraded/readiness failure, mutation boundaries stay closed, and successful provider state is never fabricated. The principal risk is semantic drift or configuration loss rather than tenant data loss. Repeated typed errors past threshold, blocked readiness, or a failing promotion proof/smoke check are alertable foundation conditions.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplesauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplesauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Because it owns no tenant mutations its audit concern is the auditable governance record: changes to the foundation move through Git history, ADRs, and validator findings, which form the durable evidence trail. Readiness and audit signals remain visible even in degraded mode so the foundation's posture is always inspectable. Audit here is about preserving honest lineage of decisions, not row-level mutation logging.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplesreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplesreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is the aggregate honesty of the foundation: a capability is ready only when its V1-proven contract, migration lineage, and proof inventory are intact and the matrix/registry/validation checks pass. Readiness fails closed when evidence is missing, stale, or unknown, and degraded mode keeps read-only readiness and audit visible. Promotion is gated on re-running the foundation matrix, registry, and validation after any fix.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplesproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplesproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Proof for this capability is the foundation matrix plus the registry and validation test that demonstrate the corpus is internally consistent and that each capability's claims are backed by evidence, not assertion. Historical demonstration is via that hermetic foundation tooling rather than live external runtime. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplessemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplesuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciplesuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The universalservicefoundationscopeandprinciples capability is explicitly internal; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionsemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "usagemeteringandmetereventingestionsemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:s80312b86457f924f105a1c1d9447ac51628ba4e28a79ffc24351b3a6cdd951f2>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:usagemeteringandmetereventingestion>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "ce32b87876350de3ef487e1fa459c8fc33440ee3e5a304c0388e9f076b302e75";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/usage-metering-and-meter-event-ingestion.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:usagemeteringandmetereventingestion> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractusagemeteringandmetereventingestion>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractusagemeteringandmetereventingestion> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractusagemeteringandmetereventingestion";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractusagemeteringandmetereventingestion>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:usagemeteringandmetereventingestion>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractusagemeteringandmetereventingestion> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractusagemeteringandmetereventingestion";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/usagemeteringandmetereventingestion.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractusagemeteringandmetereventingestion>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractusagemeteringandmetereventingestion> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractusagemeteringandmetereventingestion";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/usagemeteringandmetereventingestion.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractusagemeteringandmetereventingestion>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractusagemeteringandmetereventingestion>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractusagemeteringandmetereventingestion>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionlifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionlifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The metering lifecycle ingests meter events from operator/internal callers, validates that the meter and quantity are known, enforces the meter's entitlement, idempotently inserts the event by tenant plus meter plus idempotency key, allows explicit negative adjustments, aggregates lifetime usage, and exposes tenant and operator usage reads. Ingestion is the authoritative entry point for usage that downstream quota and billing depend on.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State is a meter catalog (meter key, entitlement key, display name, unit) plus meter-event rows containing organisation, meter, quantity, idempotency key, subject/source/metadata, and occurred-at time. The idempotency key participates in event identity so a replayed event does not double-count, and negative adjustments are stored as explicit events rather than mutating prior rows.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionpermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionpermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Meter-event ingestion is operator/internal and tenant-scoped, with usage reads available to the owning tenant and to operators for a specified tenant. Row-level isolation keys persistence by organisation so one tenant cannot read or write another tenant's usage; meter entitlement is enforced before an event is accepted.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestioncontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestioncontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The interface is a metering repository port behind which ingestion records events and queries aggregate usage, exposed through operator meter-event submission and tenant/operator usage-read operations. The contract requires a known meter, a quantity, and an idempotency key for safe ingestion.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Validation requires the meter to exist in the catalog, the quantity to be valid (including signed adjustments), and the meter's entitlement to be satisfied before the event is recorded. The idempotency key is validated so repeated submissions of the same key are deduplicated rather than aggregated twice.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionerrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionerrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Unknown meter, missing entitlement, or invalid quantity fail closed with deterministic typed outcomes and the event is not recorded. Duplicate idempotency keys resolve to the original event without double-counting, and provider unavailability returns a typed degraded failure rather than a fabricated success.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Ingestion records the event durably with subject/source/metadata so usage is attributable, and entitlement-gated rejection is observable. Audit/operational records precede or accompany the mutation rather than being reconstructed afterward.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness is proven against live relational storage covering idempotent insertion, the entitlement gate, aggregation, and row-level tenant isolation with no secret columns; route handlers and access-control metadata are validated separately. When the metering substrate is unavailable, mutation paths are disabled and readiness degrades explicitly.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by metering unit tests and runtime proofs validating live idempotency, the entitlement gate, aggregation, isolation, and route handlers. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionsemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:usagemeteringandmetereventingestionuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The usagemeteringandmetereventingestion capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:usagemeteringandmetereventingestion> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
