    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractworkflowenginescheduledjobsapprovals> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractworkflowenginescheduledjobsapprovals";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovals.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractworkflowenginescheduledjobsapprovals>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractworkflowenginescheduledjobsapprovals>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractworkflowenginescheduledjobsapprovals>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalslifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalslifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "A workflow starts into running, an approval.requested signal moves it to waiting, approval.granted completes it, approval.denied fails it, and an explicit cancel moves it to cancelled, with provider status read back through the orchestrator. Approval gates therefore drive deterministic state transitions and a denied approval fails the workflow rather than silently proceeding, while scheduled-job dispatch enqueues work onto the event substrate. Provider failure (Temporal or the in-memory orchestrator) degrades readiness and never falls back unsafely.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalsstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalsstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State comprises workflowId, workflowKey, tenantId, payload, a status of running|waiting|completed|failed|cancelled, a free-form detail field, and provider readiness, governed by a canAccess(workflowId, tenantId) predicate that binds every workflow to its owning tenant. Provider adapters map Temporal or HTTP statuses onto these canonical status values so the state machine is provider-independent. Cross-tenant access is denied by orchestrator semantics rather than by convention.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalspermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalspermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Admin workflow operations require platform.workflow.* permissions (read for inspection, write for start, signal, and cancel), while exposed tenant read surfaces use tenant.workflow.read. Workflow ids are tenant-bound and the canAccess predicate denies cross-tenant access, so an operator or tenant cannot drive or observe another tenant's workflow. Tenant context, secrets, and provider credentials do not cross the capability boundary except through the declared contract.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalscontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalscontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The contract surface is GET /api/admin/workflows, GET /api/admin/workflows/readiness, POST /api/admin/workflows/start, GET /api/admin/workflows/:workflowId, POST /api/admin/workflows/:workflowId/signal, and POST /api/admin/workflows/:workflowId/cancel, fronting a WorkflowOrchestratorPort behind the Temporal provider adapter or the in-memory orchestrator. Scheduled-job dispatch and notification requests flow outward as events after readiness checks. The port seam keeps the workflow provider swappable without changing the lifecycle contract.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalsvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalsvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Starting a workflow requires a workflow key, tenant, and workflow id; signal names drive only explicit, named transitions; a denied approval deterministically fails the workflow; and unknown workflow reads or invalid route ids surface as typed route/use-case errors. Provider adapters validate and normalise upstream status before it reaches the canonical state machine, so malformed provider responses cannot corrupt workflow state.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalserrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalserrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Errors are fail-closed: an unknown workflow read or invalid id is a typed error, an unavailable provider is a readiness/degraded state rather than a fabricated success, a denied approval yields failed, a cancel yields cancelled, and a cross-tenant access attempt returns false. Degraded mode disables mutation and side-effect paths that depend on the provider adapter while keeping read-only readiness and audit visible.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalsauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalsauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Workflow transitions emit audit-before-change records including workflow.started, workflow.approved, workflow.external_run, and workflow.completed, and where an approval grants access a support-session audit record is also written; the audit ordering is itself part of the closure and support-approval proofs. This guarantees that an approval-driven access grant is auditable before it takes effect. Audit remains producer-owned and is not inferred by downstream consumers.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalsreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalsreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness combines hermetic in-memory or local workflow-closure validation, the Temporal provider adapter and its live proof, and a dedicated workflow readiness route; the live provider proof skips honestly when its endpoints are unavailable. Provider failure degrades readiness explicitly and never upgrades hermetic closure to a live-provider claim. Closure is level-3 hermetic state-machine validation; live provider validation is level-4 when the workflow-provider profile is available.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalsproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalsproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is grounded in workflow-closure, workflow-engine, approval-workflow, workflow-adapters, temporal-workflow-provider, and workflow-provider-live proofs, captured here as informational semantic lineage from the USF coverage record and equivalence audit with no source import and an open implementation language. The proof expectation is the lineage evidence, not a current USF readiness verdict. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalsuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovalsuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovals capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:workflowenginescheduledjobsapprovals> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:writeonlysecretsettingssemanticsource> a <urn:usf:ontology:SourceSemanticBinding>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "writeonlysecretsettingssemanticsource";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingSource> <urn:usf:sourceartefact:sbbc1a2417b8d5ca8db0a4fb9a462b0bdc040d6c2ac4a967da7b3e0f45ba3f194>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:writeonlysecretsettings>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingContentDigest> "e95fddbb4f8e3f6d93d3868d02648c41ef2ae677146607e9eba60bb04a6a4f6f";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingPath> "spec/instances/semantic-contract/write-only-secret-settings.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceKind> <urn:usf:equivalencekind:structural>.
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:writeonlysecretsettings> <urn:usf:ontology:semanticLifecycleState> <urn:usf:semanticlifecyclestate:active>.
<urn:usf:repository:foundation> <urn:usf:ontology:hasArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractwriteonlysecretsettings>.
<urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractwriteonlysecretsettings> a <urn:usf:ontology:ArtefactPlan>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractwriteonlysecretsettings";
    <urn:usf:ontology:ownedByRepository> <urn:usf:repository:foundation>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansArtefact> <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractwriteonlysecretsettings>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:plansSemanticResource> <urn:usf:semanticcontract:writeonlysecretsettings>.
<urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractwriteonlysecretsettings> a <urn:usf:ontology:Artefact>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractwriteonlysecretsettings";
    <urn:usf:ontology:artefactKind> <urn:usf:artefactkind:contract>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalPath> "contracts/semantic/writeonlysecretsettings.json";
    <urn:usf:ontology:governedByPathRule> <urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractwriteonlysecretsettings>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:generatedByComponent> <urn:usf:generator:semanticcontract>.
<urn:usf:pathrule:semanticcontractwriteonlysecretsettings> a <urn:usf:ontology:PathRule>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:canonicalName> "semanticcontractwriteonlysecretsettings";
    <urn:usf:ontology:pathPattern> "contracts/semantic/writeonlysecretsettings.json".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:writeonlysecretsettingssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingArtefactPlan> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractwriteonlysecretsettings>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingEquivalenceRule> <urn:usf:equivalencerule:semanticcontractprojection>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:artefactplan:semanticcontractwriteonlysecretsettings>, <urn:usf:artefact:semanticcontractwriteonlysecretsettings>, <urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingslifecycle>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingslifecycle> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Secret-bearing settings follow a write-only lifecycle: callers create, rotate, or update a secret, the value is validated before storage where applicable, then stored encrypted, hashed, or provider-masked, after which only non-sensitive metadata such as a has-secret flag and readiness is exposed. A blank or absent secret on update preserves the existing value, and clearing occurs only through the owning resource's lifecycle rather than via a raw-read path.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:writeonlysecretsettingssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingsstatemodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingsstatemodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "State includes tenant admin credential lifecycle metadata, identity-provider secret presence with provider-masked values, secret stores for mail/webhook/API-key surfaces, and a token-crypto state distinguishing encrypted values from an explicit unencrypted test marker, all classified for readiness without ever materialising raw secret output. The persisted representation deliberately holds only protected or metadata forms of each secret.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:writeonlysecretsettingssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingspermissions>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingspermissions> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Secret writes are governed by the permissions of the owning surface (such as auth-settings write, provider-config permissions, webhook write, and API-key create/revoke scopes), and reads return only redacted metadata. Secrets are tenant-scoped through their owning resource, and there is no permission that grants retrieval of a stored raw secret.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:writeonlysecretsettingssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingscontracts>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingscontracts> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Contracts expose write-only secret fields on identity-provider create/update, credential rotation, mail-sender and webhook secret writes, and a reveal-once API-key create response, all mediated by a secret-store port with provider-backed and persistence-backed adapters. No operation in the contract supports later retrieval of a raw secret value.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:writeonlysecretsettingssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingsvalidation>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingsvalidation> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Secrets are validated before storage or provider mutation, unsafe URLs or configurations are rejected, invalid tenant credentials are classified before any store occurs, an empty identity-provider secret preserves the existing value, and encryption-key requirements are enforced for higher environments. Validation therefore runs ahead of any secret-bearing side effect.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:writeonlysecretsettingssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingserrormodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingserrormodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Outcomes are typed and fail-closed, including no-credential, invalid-credential, forbidden-realm-operation, realm-unreachable, generic validation failure, not-found, and provider-specific readiness states. Failures never echo secret material in their messages, so error handling cannot become a secret-disclosure channel.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:writeonlysecretsettingssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingsauditmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingsauditmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Audit records only safe metadata such as alias, the names of changed fields, a has-secret flag, a secret-changed flag, configuration key names, and readiness result. Audit is emitted before the secret-bearing provider or storage write, so a failed audit blocks the mutation and no raw secret value is ever audited.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:writeonlysecretsettingssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingsreadinessmodel>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingsreadinessmodel> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Readiness reports configured, missing, invalid, forbidden, unreachable, or provider-unavailable states without exposing any secret material, and provider-backed secret stores require live substrate validation to be considered ready. The capability degrades to an explicit not-ready classification rather than assuming availability.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:writeonlysecretsettingssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingsproof>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingsproof> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:complete>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "Behaviour is exercised by unit proofs over token cryptography and audit-redaction plus runtime proofs of the secret-store contract and a provider-backed secret store against a live substrate, validating that only metadata is exposed and audited. Proof is hermetic/runtime lineage; current activation evidence is recorded by the contract proof result and remains subject to freshness and invalidation.".
<urn:usf:sourcesemanticbinding:writeonlysecretsettingssemanticsource> <urn:usf:ontology:sourceBindingTarget> <urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingsuisemantics>.
<urn:usf:contractfacet:writeonlysecretsettingsuisemantics> <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatus> <urn:usf:facetstatus:notapplicable>;
    <urn:usf:ontology:facetStatement> "The writeonlysecretsettings capability is explicitly not exposed; no product or operator UI is authorised. Any UI requires a deliberate exposure amendment.".
<urn:usf:semanticcontract:writeonlysecretsettings> <urn:usf:ontology:disclaims> <urn:usf:nonclaim:nohumanacceptance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nouiproductparity>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:noaccessibilitycompliance>, <urn:usf:nonclaim:nolaunchi18n>.
